2026-02-25 15:13:11,784 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Eliminate the broken/duplicated ronly handling. Currently ronly is parsed in 3 places (authorize.js, api.js, nav-plugin.js), stored nowhere persistent, and the server-side write check is dead code. Consolidate so session.pages[pageId].ronly is the single source of truth — set once at page load, read by authorize.js for server enforcement, sent to client for UI enforcement.'}
2026-02-25 15:13:22,907 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': 'Current state:\n- `.ro` suffix on user menu perms (e.g. `inv^sa_parts.ro`) is the source of ronly\n- `authorize.js` has `hasReadOnlyPermission()` that scans raw perm strings — works but full scan per write request\n- `authorize.js` has `findMenuNode()` checking `global.$.menus` — dead code, global tree never has ronly\n- `api.js` `/api/init` re-parses `.ro` to set `ronly` on filtered menu tree nodes for client\n- `nav-plugin.js` reads `ronly` from tree widget node → sets `$.dui.ronly` (trivially bypassed)\n- `page-plugin.js` has `state.ronly` but nobody writes to it — dead field\n- `form-plugin.js` reads `$.dui.ronly` for submit block + form-lock\n\nStrategy: \n1. SERVER: pages.js already builds `session.pages[pageId]` — add `ronly` flag there by scanning udata.menus for `.ro` suffix at page load time (one-time cost)\n2. SERVER: authorize.js write check reads `session.pages[appId].ronly` — simple lookup, no scanning\n3. SERVER: api.js /api/init reads `session.pages` to set ronly on menu tree nodes instead of re-parsing\n4. CLIENT: page-plugin.js receives ronly in init/page response, sets `$.page.state.ronly`\n5. CLIENT: form-plugin.js reads `$.page.state.ronly` instead of `$.dui.ronly`\n6. CLEANUP: remove `$.dui.ronly`, `hasReadOnlyPermission()`, `findMenuNode()`, duplicate parsing'}
