2026-02-25 15:16:10,643 2113486 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 3, 'text': "Root-cause hypotheses validated:\nH1) Remote Gate Pass line write endpoint is unreliable (`No Such Field`/timeouts) -> confirmed by probe logs and fallback activation.\nH2) Fallback write path itself works -> confirmed (`add/upd/del` returned non-error fallback responses in probes).\nH3) User-visible 'cannot save' is driven by read-path visibility gap + line-number collision:\n- `handleGplines` only returns fallback rows when remote grid is empty (`lib/gatepass-fallback.js:305-317`); it does not merge fallback lines with non-empty remote line grids.\n- On existing GP with remote rows, fallback-added rows remain hidden after reload (`foundProbeLineInGridAfterAdd=false` in probe for GP-0005-18).\n- UI next line number generation uses visible grid rows only (`inv_gpass.js:39-47`), so hidden fallback line numbers are reused and `add` returns `Duplicate Record.`\n- This reproduces practical add/save failure loops for affected GP_IDs."}
