2026-02-26 08:42:12,212 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 1, 'text': '**Create modal-plugin.js** — core plugin replacing window-plugin.js + dialog-plugin.js\n\n**What exists now:**\n- `window-plugin.js` (122 lines): `$.fn.window` with open/close/destroy/setTitle + `dynDialog()` function\n- `dialog-plugin.js` (20 lines): `$.fn.dialog` alias → `$.fn.window`\n- Both use `$.data(this, \'window\')` for state\n- open() calls `showModal()` on native `<dialog>`, close() calls `.close()`\n- `dynDialog(vars, buts)` builds a `<div class="easyui-dialog">` dynamically, appends to `#_fragments_`\n\n**Critical gap — `buttons` option is NOT implemented:**\nThe current window-plugin stores `buttons` in options but never renders them. 16 page scripts pass `buttons:[{id, text, iconCls, handler}]` to `.dialog({buttons:...})`. These buttons are silently ignored today.\n\n**What modal-plugin.js must provide:**\n1. `$.fn.modal(options, param)` — primary API\n2. Methods: `open`, `close`, `destroy`, `setTitle`, `options`\n3. `buttons` option support — render button array into `.modal-action` footer\n   - Each button: `{id, text, iconCls, handler}` → render as `<button class="btn btn-sm">`\n   - Append to or replace `.modal-action` div inside modal\n4. Callbacks: `onOpen`, `onClose`, `onSave` (new)\n5. `data-action="save"` wiring — find save button, bind callback\n6. Form access: `$(\'#id\').modal(\'form\')` → returns the `<form>` inside modal-box\n7. State stored as `$.data(this, \'modal\')`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `public/dui/js/plugins/modal-plugin.js`\n- Position in build: replaces window-plugin.js + dialog-plugin.js slots (lines 31-32 of build script)\n\n**Page scripts using `.dialog({buttons:[...]})` (16 call sites):**\n- calendar.js, wip_count.js, physical_count.js, cp_man.js (inv+vwltsa), sa_jobman.js, rent_man.js, pn_config.js, sa_ship.js, purchase_receipt.js, sa_sorder.js, quote_man.js, qp_qpman.js\n\n**Page scripts using `.window({...})` (7 call sites):**\n- sa_parts.js, sa_jobplan.js, maint_man.js, capor_inc.js, sa_sorder_otd_inc.js, cp_man_inc.js, quote_man.js'}
2026-02-26 08:42:22,733 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 2, 'text': "**Alias $.fn.dialog and $.fn.window → $.fn.modal**\n\n**What exists now:**\n- `$.fn.dialog` (dialog-plugin.js:9) — delegates to `$.fn.window`\n- `$.fn.window` (window-plugin.js:15) — the real implementation\n- Page scripts call both interchangeably: `.dialog('open')`, `.window('open')`, `.dialog({buttons:...})`, `.window({onOpen:...})`\n\n**What to do:**\n- In modal-plugin.js, after defining `$.fn.modal`, add:\n  ```js\n  $.fn.dialog = $.fn.modal;\n  $.fn.dialog.methods = $.fn.modal.methods;\n  $.fn.dialog.defaults = $.fn.modal.defaults;\n  $.fn.window = $.fn.modal;\n  $.fn.window.methods = $.fn.modal.methods;\n  $.fn.window.defaults = $.fn.modal.defaults;\n  ```\n- All existing `.dialog('open')` / `.window('open')` / `.dialog({buttons:...})` calls continue working unchanged\n- State key should be `'modal'` internally, but check for legacy `'window'` data too for any init-time edge cases\n\n**Verification:**\n- grep all `.dialog(` and `.window(` calls in `html/dui/mod/` — count ~90 call sites total\n- Every method used: open, close, destroy, setTitle, resize, move, options\n- `resize` and `move` are used by sa_parts.js, pn_gen.js, capor_inc.js, files.js — need stub or implementation"}
2026-02-26 08:42:36,937 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 3, 'text': '**Move dynDialog into modal-plugin.js**\n\n**What exists now:**\n- `dynDialog(vars, buts)` defined in window-plugin.js lines 102-115\n- Exposed as `$.dui.fn.dynDialog` and shimmed to `window.dynDialog`\n- Builds a `<div class="easyui-dialog">` with fields from `dynadd()`, appends to `#_fragments_`\n- Calls `$.parser.parse(\'#_fragments_\')` then `ebox.dialog({buttons: buts})`\n- If dialog already exists (same id), returns existing one without recreating\n\n**Pages using dynDialog (3):**\n1. `admin/js/sysbut.js:11` — Send User Message dialog (textbox field)\n2. `admin/js/logins.js:242` — Same Send User Message dialog  \n3. `vwltsa/js/wo_bas.inc.js:109` — Import BOM from Part dialog (combobox field)\n\n**What to do:**\n- Move dynDialog function into modal-plugin.js\n- Keep same signature: `dynDialog(vars, buts)` → returns jQuery element\n- Keep `$.dui.fn.dynDialog` and `window.dynDialog` shim\n- Optionally add `$.modal.create(opts)` as the modern API (same internals)\n- dynDialog currently creates `<div class="easyui-dialog">` — should create native `<dialog class="modal">` instead\n\n**#_fragments_ mount point:**\n- EUI layout has `div#_fragments_(style="display:none;")` at html/eui/layout.pug:106\n- DUI layout does NOT have it — needs to be added to `html/dui/layout/main.pug` or created dynamically by the plugin if missing'}
2026-02-26 08:42:55,825 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 4, 'text': '**Update +modal mixin — auto-generate form, detect existing manual form**\n\n**What exists now (feedback.pug lines 45-61):**\n```pug\nmixin modal(opts = {})\n  dialog.modal(id=id, ...)\n    .modal-box.p-6(style=style, class=boxCls)\n      if title\n        h3.font-bold.mb-4= title\n      block\n    .modal-backdrop: button(onclick="this.closest(\'dialog\').close()")\n```\n- No form wrapper — authors must add `+form` manually inside block\n- Datagrid editor modal (datagrid.pug:96-137) uses `+modal` and puts `+fitem` fields directly — no form wrapper today\n\n**What to change:**\n- Auto-wrap block content in `form(id=modalId + \'-form\')` inside `.modal-box`\n- Detect if block already contains a manual `form` element — if so, skip auto-form\n  - Detection approach: use a flag variable `_modalAutoForm` that `+form` mixin sets when called inside a modal block. If flag is set after block renders, skip wrapper.\n  - Alternative: render block into a variable, check for `<form` in output, wrap if absent\n  - Simplest: always emit form wrapper, rely on authors NOT using `+form` inside modal (since it\'s now automatic)\n- Form ID convention: `{modalId}-form` (e.g. `#mymodal` → `#mymodal-form`)\n\n**Impact on existing pug templates using +modal:**\n- datagrid.pug editor modal — no manual form → gets auto-form (bonus)\n- Any page with `+modal` containing `+form` manually → need to verify these don\'t double-wrap\n- Pages with `+dialog` / `+window` aliases → inherits same auto-form via pass-through\n\n**Note:** The `+form` mixin (in form.pug) generates form tag + hidden fields (_func, _sqlid, etc). The auto-form in modal should be a plain `<form>` wrapper, NOT the full `+form` mixin, since modal forms may not need _func/_sqlid hidden fields.'}
2026-02-26 08:43:04,746 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 5, 'text': "**Update +dialog and +window aliases — pass through auto-form**\n\n**What exists now (feedback.pug lines 110-119):**\n```pug\nmixin dialog(opts = {})\n  +modal&attributes(attributes)\n    block\n\nmixin window(opts = {})\n  +modal&attributes(attributes)\n    block\n```\n- Both pass through to `+modal` with all attributes and block content\n- Auto-form from step 4 will automatically flow through since these are pure pass-throughs\n\n**What to verify:**\n- Confirm that `&attributes(attributes)` correctly forwards id, title, style, max-w, closed, modal, iconCls\n- Confirm block content passes through to modal's block (which will be auto-wrapped in form)\n- No changes needed IF +modal auto-form works correctly — these are already thin pass-throughs\n\n**This step may be a no-op** — just verification that the aliases still work after step 4 changes."}
2026-02-26 08:43:16,362 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 6, 'text': "**Retire window-plugin.js and dialog-plugin.js — remove from bundle**\n\n**What to do:**\n1. Delete `public/dui/js/plugins/window-plugin.js` (122 lines)\n2. Delete `public/dui/js/plugins/dialog-plugin.js` (20 lines)\n3. Update `scripts/build-dui-plugins.sh`:\n   - Remove lines 31-32 (`window-plugin.js`, `dialog-plugin.js`)\n   - Add `modal-plugin.js` in their place (single file)\n   - Must load AFTER panel-plugin.js and linkbutton-plugin.js (for button rendering)\n   - Must load BEFORE messager-plugin.js and datagrid-plugin.js (they use modal/dialog API)\n4. Rebuild bundle: `npm run dui:plugins`\n\n**Dependency check:**\n- `dynDialog` depends on `dynadd()` from dynadd-plugin.js (loads later at line 43)\n  - This means dynDialog can't call dynadd at define-time, only at call-time — should be fine since it's invoked by page scripts after all plugins load\n- `$.parser.parseOptions` used in window-plugin.js — modal-plugin needs parser-plugin (loads early at line 14) ✓\n- `$.dui.shim` from dui-namespace.js (line 13) ✓\n\n**Risk:** Zero risk to existing code since all public API surface (`$.fn.dialog`, `$.fn.window`, `dynDialog`) stays identical via the new modal-plugin."}
2026-02-26 08:43:30,299 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 7, 'text': '**Write docs/dui/modal.md**\n\n**Sections to cover:**\n\n1. **Overview** — Native `<dialog>` modal with DaisyUI styling, auto-form wrapper, backward-compat aliases\n2. **Pug Mixins** — `+modal`, `+modal-footer`, `+dialog` (alias), `+window` (alias)\n   - Parameters: id, title, style, max-w\n   - Auto-form: form id convention `{modalId}-form`\n   - Block content: +fitem fields go directly in modal, form wrapper is automatic\n3. **JS API** — `$.fn.modal` methods\n   - open, close, destroy, setTitle, options, form\n   - `$.fn.dialog` and `$.fn.window` as aliases\n4. **Buttons** — `buttons` option format: `[{id, text, iconCls, handler}]`\n   - Rendered into `.modal-action` footer\n   - Example from calendar.js pattern\n5. **Callbacks** — onOpen, onClose, onSave\n6. **data-action pattern** — `data-action="save"` on buttons, wired by plugin\n7. **dynDialog** — Dynamic dialog builder: `dynDialog(vars, buts)` / `$.modal.create(opts)`\n   - Field definitions, button definitions\n8. **Examples** — Common patterns: simple modal, modal with save, datagrid editor modal\n9. **Notes** — Migration from EUI, backward compat guarantees\n\n**File:** `docs/dui/modal.md`'}
2026-02-26 08:43:38,760 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 8, 'text': "**Update UI Help page — Modal component examples and output**\n\n**What to update:**\n- `html/dui/mod/dev/js/ui_help.js` — add Modal section handler\n  - Load docs/dui/modal.md content into Overview, Mixins, Parameters, Examples, JS API, Notes tabs\n  - Show rendered modal example in Output tab\n- Modal is already in the Component dropdown (added previously as `{text:'Modal',value:'modal'}`)\n\n**Example content to show:**\n- Pug: simple modal with fitem fields and modal-footer\n- Output: rendered HTML showing `<dialog>` → `.modal-box` → `<form>` → fields → `.modal-action`\n- JS API: open/close/buttons methods\n- Notes: auto-form behaviour, backward compat aliases"}
2026-02-26 08:43:52,086 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 9, 'text': '**Test across pages — verify all modal patterns still work**\n\n**Test cases by pattern:**\n\n1. **Datagrid editor modal** — sa_parts A8000 BOM tab (or inv_gpass)\n   - Add/Edit/Delete row → modal opens, fields populate, save works, modal closes\n   - data-action="save" button wiring\n\n2. **dynDialog** — admin/logins or admin/sysbut page\n   - Click "Send Message" → dynDialog creates dialog dynamically\n   - Fields render, button click works, dialog closes\n\n3. **`.dialog({buttons:[...]})` pattern** — co/calendar page\n   - Dialog opens with Clone/Delete/Save/Close buttons rendered in footer\n   - Each button handler fires correctly\n\n4. **`.window({onOpen:...})` pattern** — inv/sa_parts Part Number Generator\n   - `$(\'#pngenwin\').window({...})` initialises, `.window(\'open\')` shows modal\n   - `.window(\'move\', ...)` and `.window(\'resize\', ...)` calls don\'t throw\n\n5. **Simple `.dialog(\'open\')` / `.dialog(\'close\')`** — multiple pages\n   - dqm/gauge_man: `$(\'#gaugerenameopt\').dialog(\'open\'/\'close\')`\n   - vwltsa/sa_jobman: multiple dialogs (cloneopt, addsub, grl, importopt)\n\n6. **Page isolation** — navigate between pages, verify no state leaks\n\n7. **Console errors** — check for any JS errors after each test'}
2026-02-26 08:44:05,950 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 10, 'text': "**Deferred: migrate existing pages to new modal pattern**\n\n**What this means:**\nConvert existing page scripts from legacy EUI patterns to the new modal API. This is cosmetic cleanup — everything works via aliases, so this is purely optional code modernisation.\n\n**Patterns to convert:**\n1. `.dialog('open')` / `.dialog('close')` → `.modal('open')` / `.modal('close')`\n2. `.window('open')` / `.window('close')` → `.modal('open')` / `.modal('close')`\n3. `.dialog({buttons:[...]})` → buttons already work, but could move to pug +modal-footer with data-action buttons\n4. Manual `+form` inside `+modal` → remove (auto-form handles it)\n5. `dynDialog(vars, buts)` → `$.modal.create(opts)` (modern API)\n\n**Pages affected (~30+ files):**\n- inv: sa_parts, cp_man, cp_man_inc, purchase_receipt, inv_gpass, pn_gen, pn_config, wip_count, physical_count\n- vwltsa: sa_jobman, sa_jobplan, sa_operators, wo_bas.inc, maint_man, lt_allocate, cp_man, capor_inc, dg_filter.inc, pn_gen\n- dqm: gauge_man, coc_man, qp_qpman, rent_man, caas_aw95\n- sales: sa_ship, sa_sorder, sa_sorder_otd_inc, quote_man\n- admin: sysbut, logins, files, reports, global\n- co: calendar\n\n**This step is deferred** — do not implement unless explicitly asked. The backward-compat aliases mean all existing code works unchanged."}
2026-02-26 08:58:19,585 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '**Steps:**\n1. Create modal-plugin.js — core plugin with $.fn.modal, open/close, data-action button wiring, callbacks\n2. Alias $.fn.dialog and $.fn.window to $.fn.modal — backward compat\n3. Move dynDialog into modal-plugin.js — keep old shim, use $.modal.create() underneath\n4. Update +modal mixin in feedback.pug — auto-generate form, detect existing manual form and skip\n5. Update +dialog and +window aliases — pass through auto-form behaviour\n6. Retire window-plugin.js and dialog-plugin.js — remove from bundle\n7. Update docs/dui/modal.md — new API, auto-form, form ID convention, data-action pattern\n8. Update UI Help page — Modal component examples and output to match\n9. Test across pages — datagrid editor, print dialog, part generator, dynDialog pages\n10. (Deferred) Migrate existing pages — convert manual form/footer patterns to new modal API\n\n**Key Findings from Discovery:**\n- **~90 call sites** across 30+ page scripts use `.dialog()` or `.window()`\n- **16 pages pass `buttons:[{id, text, iconCls, handler}]`** to `.dialog({buttons:...})` — currently silently ignored by window-plugin (critical gap to fix)\n- **3 pages use `dynDialog()`** — sysbut.js, logins.js, wo_bas.inc.js\n- **`#_fragments_` mount point** exists in EUI layout (layout.pug:106) but missing from DUI layout — needed for dynDialog, create dynamically if absent\n- **`resize` and `move` methods** called by ~5 pages (sa_parts, pn_gen, capor_inc, files) — need stubs at minimum\n- **Steps 1-3** are the heavy lifting (new plugin + aliases + dynDialog)\n- **Step 4** is the mixin change (auto-form)\n- **Step 5** is likely a no-op (aliases already pass through to +modal)\n- **Step 6** is cleanup (delete old files, update build script)\n- **Steps 7-8** are docs\n- **Step 9** is testing across all modal patterns\n- **Step 10** is deferred — backward-compat aliases mean all existing code works unchanged'}
