2026-02-26 11:08:53,038 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'remote-udata', 'kind': 'goal', 'text': '**RECURRING BUG — 6th occurrence. This MUST be permanently resolved.**\n\n`_udata` (the entire user session object — userid, groups, menus, permissions) is being injected into `req.query` by Express middleware (`lib/pages.js:190`) for pug template rendering. The sqlid proxy (`lib/endpoints.js`) then merges `req.query` into `allParams`, and since `_udata` starts with `_`, it gets forwarded to the remote data server\'s URL query string.\n\n**The root architectural rule (from MEMORY.md):**\n- Browser request and remote server request are TWO COMPLETELY SEPARATE REQUESTS — NEVER merge them\n- `_udata` is injected by Express middleware — it must NEVER be forwarded to the remote server\n- `_udata` should ONLY be injected very late in the route, and ONLY for two purposes:\n  1. Rendering pug templates (res.locals / pug locals for group checks like PART-UD)\n  2. Sending data back to the browser\n- It must NEVER be present on `req.query` or `req.body` at the point where the sqlid proxy reads those objects\n\n**Current state of the code:**\n- `lib/pages.js:190` — `req.query._udata = udata` — injects session data into query for pug templates\n- `lib/endpoints.js:99-103` — `allParams = Object.assign({}, queryParams, bodyParams)` — merges everything including `_udata`\n- `lib/endpoints.js:109-111` — `_udata` starts with `_`, so it goes into `remoteQuery` → forwarded to remote server URL\n- `proxyStream` (line 260) has a manual `delete query._udata` but `processSqlIdRequest` does NOT\n\n**Impact:** Remote server receives `_udata` as a query parameter → "No Such Field" errors, 500 errors, silent save failures. This triggered the entire gatepass-fallback shadow data store (now disabled) which masked the real problem for weeks.\n\n**This is the 6th time this issue has surfaced. The fix must be structural, not another band-aid delete statement.**'}
2026-02-26 11:16:52,829 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'remote-udata', 'kind': 'goal', 'text': '**RECURRING BUG — 6th occurrence. This MUST be permanently resolved.**\n\n`_udata` (the entire user session object — userid, groups, menus, permissions) is being injected into `req.query` by Express middleware (`lib/pages.js:190`) for pug template rendering. The sqlid proxy (`lib/endpoints.js`) then merges `req.query` into `allParams`, and since `_udata` starts with `_`, it gets forwarded to the remote data server\'s URL query string.\n\n**The root architectural rule (from MEMORY.md):**\n- Browser request and remote server request are TWO COMPLETELY SEPARATE REQUESTS — NEVER merge them\n- `_udata` is injected by Express middleware — it must NEVER be forwarded to the remote server\n- `_udata` should ONLY be injected very late in the route, and ONLY for two purposes:\n  1. Rendering pug templates (res.locals / pug locals for group checks like PART-UD)\n  2. Sending data back to the browser\n- It must NEVER be present on `req.query` or `req.body` at the point where the sqlid proxy reads those objects\n\n**Current state of the code:**\n- `lib/pages.js:190` — `req.query._udata = udata` — injects session data into query for pug templates\n- `lib/endpoints.js:99-103` — `allParams = Object.assign({}, queryParams, bodyParams)` — merges everything including `_udata`\n- `lib/endpoints.js:109-111` — `_udata` starts with `_`, so it goes into `remoteQuery` → forwarded to remote server URL\n- `proxyStream` (line 260) has a manual `delete query._udata` but `processSqlIdRequest` does NOT\n\n**Impact:** Remote server receives `_udata` as a query parameter → "No Such Field" errors, 500 errors, silent save failures. This triggered the entire gatepass-fallback shadow data store (now disabled) which masked the real problem for weeks.\n\n**Root cause:** `req.query._udata` is completely unnecessary. `res.locals.udata` is already set at `pages.js:186` — every pug template already has access to `udata` directly via locals. The `req.query._udata` injection was redundant from the start. The only consumer (`sa_parts.pug`) uses `locals.req.query._udata` because it was copied verbatim from the EUI original — it should have been `locals.udata` all along.\n\n**Fix:** Remove `req.query._udata` injection entirely. 4 lines changed, problem eliminated structurally.\n\n**This is the 6th time this issue has surfaced. The fix must be structural, not another band-aid delete statement.**'}
2026-02-26 11:16:56,559 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_delete args={'number': 1, 'task': 'remote-udata'}
