2026-02-26 13:08:07,837 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'patch-260226a', 'description': 'Iterative converter improvements based on sa_parts.pug.ref diff:\n1. +split → +vsplit/+hsplit with size hoisted from child panel\n2. Strip jQuery Mobile classes: .ui-grid-a, .ui-block-a, .ui.block-b\n3. .hide → .hidden (EUI → DUI visibility)\n4. Fix </form> not being removed by inline HTML fixer\n5. .linkbutton → .btn in style blocks\n6. data-options on +tabs — check DUI tab handling'}
2026-02-26 13:08:59,229 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': '## Requirements from sa_parts.pug.ref diff analysis\n\n### 1. +split → +vsplit/+hsplit with size hoisting (BIGGEST)\n- Converter currently outputs `+split` + `+panel(\'west\', { style: "width:400px" })`\n- Ref expects `+vsplit(\'400px\')` + `+panel(\'west\')` (bare)\n- `+split` is deprecated — must NEVER appear in output\n- Logic: scan child panels after converting layout:\n  - west/east child → parent becomes `+vsplit(size)`, size from child\'s width\n  - north/south child → parent becomes `+hsplit(size)`, size from child\'s height\n- Strip size from child panel after hoisting to parent\n\n### 2. Strip jQuery Mobile grid classes\n- `.ui-grid-a` → remove (CSS grid handles layout via .two/.three)\n- `.ui-block-a` → remove\n- `.ui.block-b` → remove (note: `.ui.block-b` is actually `.ui` + `.block-b`, both meaningless)\n- These are jQuery Mobile column layout artifacts, DUI uses CSS grid\n\n### 3. .hide → .hidden\n- EUI uses `.hide` for visibility\n- DUI uses `.hidden` (Tailwind utility)\n- Simple class rename\n\n### 4. </form> not removed\n- `fixInlineHtmlForm()` should handle `</form>` but it\'s not catching line 116\n- The `</form>` is indented inside tab content — may be an indentation issue\n- Need to verify the fixer runs and catches all `</form>` occurrences\n\n### 5. .linkbutton → .btn in style blocks\n- Line 4: `.linkbutton + .linkbutton` is EUI class\n- DUI equivalent is `.btn + .btn`\n- This is inside a `style.` block, not a class attribute — needs text replacement in CSS blocks\n\n### 6. data-options on +tabs\n- `+tabs#ptabs(data-options="fit:true, tabPosition:\'left\'")` — EUI pattern\n- DUI tabs plugin may handle data-options, but should verify\n- tabPosition:\'left\' is already handled by the ref (kept as-is), so likely OK for now\n\n### Additional findings\n- `#addmenu.menu.hide` → `.hide` should become `.hidden` (item 3 above)\n- The `</form>` on line 116 is the closing tag for the inline HTML `<form>` on lines 27-31 — the fixer handles `</form>` but this one survives because the `<form>` lines themselves are kept as inline HTML (they\'re inside pug conditionals and can\'t be converted to +form mixin)'}
2026-02-26 13:13:21,373 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': '## Deprecation warning approach\nInstead of injecting console.warn into converted pages, add the deprecation warning to the `+split` mixin itself in layout.pug. When the page is manually fixed to use +vsplit/+hsplit, the warning disappears automatically.\n\nSame pattern can be used for any other deprecated mixin calls — the warning lives in the mixin, not the page.'}
