2026-02-26 13:25:09,582 2264818 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'gatepass-cust-vendor-id-not-populated', 'kind': 'plan', 'text': '1) Reproduce in browser — load Gate Pass, open an existing record, confirm Cust/Vendor ID is blank and note which view (header form or line grid) is affected.\n2) Read the Pug template (inv_gpass.pug) — locate the Cust/Vendor ID field, check its name/id attribute and any data binding.\n3) Read the JS config (inv_gpass.js and any datagrid JSON) — find the field/column definition for Cust/Vendor ID, check the field key used.\n4) Inspect the API response — use browser devtools or curl to capture the raw data returned for a Gate Pass record; confirm whether the field key exists and has a value in the payload.\n5) Cross-reference — compare the field key in the template/JS against the key in the API response to identify any mismatch, missing mapping, or rendering gap.\n6) Check new vs edit scenarios — determine if the field is blank only on new records, only on existing, or both.\n7) Write up findings with exact file/line references and the identified root cause.'}
