2026-02-26 13:29:44,682 2264818 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 4, 'text': "The API (inv^gp_head) does return GP_TYPE_ID with a valid value (customer or vendor ID). The form-plugin calls combobox('setValue', value) during load (form-plugin.js L176). However, since the combobox has no options loaded at that point, setValue sets the hidden input but the visible text stays blank (editable:false means it cannot fall back to showing the raw value). The problem is not in the API response — the data is correct. The problem is entirely frontend: the combobox has no options to resolve the value against."}
2026-02-26 13:29:49,286 2264818 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_done args={'number': 4}
2026-02-26 13:30:06,103 2264818 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_switch args={'number': 5}
2026-02-26 13:30:54,578 2264818 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 5, 'text': "Field name is NOT mismatched. Template uses name='GP_TYPE_ID' (pug L13), JS initializes $('#GP_TYPE_ID').combobox() (JS L256) — matches correctly.\n\nThe binding issue is a missing options-load step. The combobox _sqlid is deliberately left empty ('') at init. The only code that sets it is the GP_TYPE.onSelect handler (JS L246-252):\n  cv.combobox('options').queryParams._sqlid = {'C':'sales^custid','V':'inv^vendorid'}[rec.value];\n  cv.combobox('reload');\n\nThis handler only fires on user interaction (clicking GP_TYPE). It is never called programmatically during form data load. So when an existing record is loaded, _sqlid stays '' and onBeforeLoad (JS L266-268) returns false — the combobox never fetches its options list."}
2026-02-26 13:31:41,477 2264818 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_done args={'number': 5}
2026-02-26 13:31:49,276 2264818 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_switch args={'number': 6}
2026-02-26 13:32:17,640 2264818 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 6, 'text': "New record scenario (but_add L289-303):\n  - GP_TYPE and GP_TYPE_ID are set to readonly=false\n  - GP_TYPE_ID combobox _sqlid is still ''\n  - User MUST manually select GP_TYPE first → onSelect fires → _sqlid is set → reload() is called → options load → user can then select GP_TYPE_ID\n  - This path WORKS because the user triggers onSelect before touching GP_TYPE_ID\n\nExisting record scenario (form loadDone L310-312 → afterLoad → loadData L4-49):\n  - form-plugin populates all fields via combobox('setValue') — GP_TYPE shows correctly (has static data), GP_TYPE_ID setValue runs but combobox has no options (blank shown)\n  - loadData() then makes GP_TYPE_ID readonly (L7) — but never sets _sqlid or calls reload()\n  - Result: GP_TYPE_ID is blank and readonly — user cannot fix it themselves\n\nConclusion: blank ONLY on existing record load. New records work because the user interaction triggers the correct load sequence."}
2026-02-26 13:32:27,413 2264818 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_done args={'number': 6}
2026-02-26 13:32:28,896 2264818 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_switch args={'number': 7}
2026-02-26 13:33:07,338 2264818 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 7, 'text': "ROOT CAUSE: loadData() never initialises GP_TYPE_ID combobox options before making the field readonly\n\nFull evidence chain:\n\n1. Template (inv_gpass.pug:13)\n   GP_TYPE_ID is a combobox with no static data and no _sqlid attribute — options must come from JS.\n\n2. JS init (inv_gpass.js:256-268)\n   $('#GP_TYPE_ID').combobox({ _sqlid: '', ... onBeforeLoad: function(qp){ if(!qp._sqlid) return false; } })\n   _sqlid starts empty. onBeforeLoad guard prevents any load while _sqlid is ''.\n\n3. The only _sqlid setter (inv_gpass.js:246-252) — inside GP_TYPE.onSelect:\n   cv.combobox('options').queryParams._sqlid = {'C':'sales^custid','V':'inv^vendorid'}[rec.value];\n   cv.combobox('reload');\n   This only fires on USER interaction with GP_TYPE, not on programmatic form load.\n\n4. loadData() (inv_gpass.js:4-49) — the afterLoad hook called when a record is loaded:\n   - L6: $('#GP_TYPE').textbox('readonly')       ← works, GP_TYPE has static options\n   - L7: $('#GP_TYPE_ID').textbox('readonly')    ← makes field readonly BUT never sets _sqlid or reloads\n   - L17: reads GP_TYPE value for doc type logic ← proves GP_TYPE IS populated correctly\n   No code here sets GP_TYPE_ID._sqlid or calls reload().\n\n5. form-plugin.js:176 — during form load, calls combobox('setValue', value) on GP_TYPE_ID.\n   GP_TYPE_ID combobox has zero options at this point → setValue stores the hidden value\n   but display text stays blank (editable:false prevents fallback raw display).\n\nAFFECTED SCENARIO: Existing record load only.\nNEW RECORD: Not affected — user selects GP_TYPE → onSelect fires → _sqlid set → reload() → options load → user picks GP_TYPE_ID.\nEXISTING RECORD: Broken — loadData() locks the field readonly without ever loading its options. User cannot recover.\n\nFIX DIRECTION (not implemented):\nIn loadData(), after reading gptype (L17), add:\n  var cv = $('#GP_TYPE_ID');\n  var sqlid = {'C':'sales^custid','V':'inv^vendorid'}[gptype];\n  if (sqlid) {\n    cv.combobox('options').queryParams._sqlid = sqlid;\n    cv.combobox('reload');  // or loadData then setValue after reload completes\n  }"}
