2026-02-26 14:19:27,467 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 17, 'text': '## Findings: qbe→combobox conversion is wrong for fkey/navi fields\n\n### Root cause\nThe converter\'s `fixQbeToCombobox` renames `class:\'qbe\'` → `class:\'combobox\'` and injects `_sqlid` from qbedef.js. This breaks fkey navigation fields like Gate Pass ID because:\n\n1. **EUI qbe** renders `<input type="text">` — typeahead/picker, queries on demand with `_dgrid=y`, handles thousands of records via filtering\n2. **DUI combobox** renders `<select>` — eagerly loads ALL rows at page load with `_combo=y`\n3. `$(\'#GP_ID\').qbe({defid:\'gatepass_ids\'})` in the page JS silently bails on `<select>` elements — becomes a no-op\n4. `valueField` mismatch: qbedef says `GP_ID`, combobox defaults to `value` — options appear blank\n\n### Solution\nStop renaming `qbe` → `combobox`. The `+qbe` mixin in `input.pug:617` already aliases to `+combobox`, so the rendering is handled.\n\n### What to change in `fixQbeToCombobox`\n- Keep the `_sqlid` injection (still valuable — ensures the field gets its data source)\n- Do NOT rename `qbe` to `combobox` in the class attribute\n- Do NOT add the `//- [auto] qbe→combobox:` comment line\n- Just inject `_sqlid` into the existing line if missing\n\n### Impact\n- All pages with qbe fkey fields (Gate Pass, Part ID, etc.) will keep working\n- The qbe-plugin.js handles the typeahead behavior on `<input>` elements\n- When the qbe class goes through `input.pug`, the `+qbe` mixin renders it as a combobox `<select>`\n- The JS `.qbe({defid:...})` call will either enhance it (if `<input>`) or bail (if `<select>` — which is fine since combobox already handles selection)'}
