2026-02-26 14:45:03,795 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 18, 'text': "## Fix: qbe-plugin.js select element support\n\n### Problem\nqbe-plugin.js bails at line 387-390 when element is `<select>`. After EUI→DUI conversion, +qbe aliases to +combobox which renders `<select>`. Page JS calls `.qbe({defid:...})` which stores state but loads no data.\n\n### Solution\nRemove the `<select>` bail-out. When `isSelect`:\n1. Skip custom dropdown UI build (not needed — native `<select>` handles selection)\n2. Skip typeahead event handlers (not applicable to `<select>`)\n3. **Load data** from qbedef's `_sqlid` using `_combo:'y'` format and populate via `.combobox('loadData', rows)`\n4. Multi-column search/filter table = no-op stub (QBE table feature deferred)\n5. All combobox API methods work as-is since underlying element is `<select>` managed by combobox-plugin\n\n### Key insight from user\nQBE is a combobox + search table overlay. The page used plain combobox for 2 years before QBE was added. All API methods (onLoad, getData, etc.) are identical — only the initial selection UX differs."}
