2026-02-26 15:24:05,502 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': '## QBE Plugin — Full Implementation\n\n### What QBE is\n- A combobox with a multi-column search/filter table overlay\n- Built on top of combobox — all API methods (getValue, setValue, onSelect, etc.) are identical\n- Only the selection UX differs: instead of picking from a simple dropdown, user gets a searchable multi-column grid\n- Combobox existed for 2 years before QBE was added on top\n\n### Current state in DUI\n- qbe-plugin.js has a working typeahead implementation for `<input>` elements — debounced search, multi-column dropdown, prev/next navi\n- But `+qbe` mixin aliases to `+combobox` → renders `<select>` → plugin bypasses all that and just loads combo data (patch-260226c)\n- So right now QBE fields work as plain comboboxes — functional but missing the search/filter table\n- combobox-plugin fixes (onBeforeLoad param order, setValues cascading, autoload queuing) also landed today\n\n### Open questions\n- How does the EUI QBE dialog actually work (full modal/table/filter UX)?\n- Should QBE remain a `<select>` with a table popover, or become an `<input>` with a custom dropdown?\n- How should `onDemand` vs `preload` behave in DUI context?\n- Full scope of qbedef configurations across all pages?\n- How does this interact with datagrid editor QBE fields (inline editing in grids)?'}
2026-02-26 15:33:25,887 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': "## QBE Plugin — Full Implementation\n\n### What QBE is\n- A combobox + modal datagrid for value selection\n- All combobox API methods are identical (getValue, setValue, onSelect, etc.)\n- The `<select>` is the visible field showing the selected value\n- Instead of picking from a native dropdown, user gets a modal (`$.modal.new()`) with a full datagrid\n- Datagrid columns come from `qbedef.fields`, each with editors for filtering\n- User filters by columns, selects a row, that row's value populates the combobox\n\n### Key differences from plain combobox\n1. **Big data** — can't eagerly load all options, needs server-side filtering with pagination (`_dgrid:'y'`, `_rows`, `_page`)\n2. **Selection via modal** — `$.modal.new()` with datagrid inside\n3. **Filterable columns** — qbedef fields have editors so user can filter/search by any column\n4. **Row selection** — user picks a row, value populates the combobox\n\n### Current state in DUI\n- qbe-plugin.js has a working typeahead implementation for `<input>` elements — debounced search, multi-column dropdown, prev/next navi\n- But `+qbe` mixin aliases to `+combobox` → renders `<select>` → plugin bypasses all that and just loads combo data (patch-260226c)\n- So right now QBE fields work as plain comboboxes — functional but missing the modal datagrid picker\n- combobox-plugin fixes (onBeforeLoad param order, setValues cascading, autoload queuing) also landed today\n\n### Open questions\n- How should `onDemand` vs `preload` behave in DUI context?\n- Full scope of qbedef configurations across all pages?\n- How does this interact with datagrid editor QBE fields (inline editing in grids)?"}
2026-02-26 15:42:51,296 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': "## QBE Plugin — Full Implementation\n\n### What QBE is\n- A combobox + modal datagrid for value selection\n- All combobox API methods are identical (getValue, setValue, onSelect, etc.)\n- The `<select>` is the visible field showing the selected value\n- Instead of picking from a native dropdown, user gets a modal (`$.modal.new()`) with a full datagrid\n- Datagrid columns come from `qbedef.fields`, each with editors for filtering\n- User filters by columns, selects a row, that row's value populates the combobox\n\n### Key differences from plain combobox\n1. **Big data** — can't eagerly load all options, needs server-side filtering with pagination (`_dgrid:'y'`, `_rows`, `_page`)\n2. **Selection via modal** — `$.modal.new()` with datagrid inside\n3. **Filterable columns** — qbedef fields have editors so user can filter/search by any column\n4. **Row selection** — user picks a row, value populates the combobox, modal closes\n\n### Phase 1 requirements\n1. Add a search icon button to the qbe combobox (alongside existing navi buttons)\n2. Clicking opens `$.modal.new()` containing a `+datagrid()`\n3. Datagrid columns/fields from qbedef definition\n4. Data loaded from qbedef's `_sqlid` with `_dgrid:'y'`\n5. Row select → `$('#field').combobox('select', row[valueField])` → modal closes\n6. The combobox `select` method triggers onSelect → formLoad cascade automatically\n\n### Design rules — ABSOLUTE\n- Use `+modal()`, `+datagrid()` and existing DUI mixins — no raw HTML generation\n- All styling via DaisyUI/Tailwind utility classes — no inline fontSize, color, background overrides\n- No hardcoded hex colors or pixel font sizes — everything follows the theme\n- Search icon button uses existing button patterns (`.btn`, icon classes)\n- Modal and datagrid look identical to any other modal/datagrid in the system\n- Zero custom CSS. If a mixin doesn't support something, extend the mixin — don't bypass it\n\n### Current state in DUI\n- qbe-plugin.js has typeahead for `<input>` elements + `<select>` data loading (patch-260226c)\n- `+qbe` mixin aliases to `+combobox` → renders `<select>`\n- combobox-plugin fixes landed: onBeforeLoad param order, setValues cascading, autoload queuing\n\n### Open questions\n- How does this interact with datagrid editor QBE fields (inline editing in grids)?"}
2026-02-26 15:44:42,097 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Phase 1 Implementation Plan\n\n### Architecture\nQBE search is added entirely in qbe-plugin.js. No new plugins needed. The plugin detects `<select>` elements with `qbe` class, adds a search button, and wires it to a modal datagrid.\n\n### Step-by-step\n\n#### 1. Add search icon button to qbe combobox (input.pug)\n- In the navi branch (line 184-195), detect `hasQbe` = `classList.includes(\'qbe\')`\n- Add a search button BEFORE the navi buttons: `button.btn.btn-sm.btn-ghost.join-item.qbe-search(type="button" tabindex="-1")` with `span.w-4.h-4(data-lucide="search")`\n- For non-navi qbe combos, wrap in `.join.w-full` and add the search button\n- Button uses same `.btn.btn-sm.btn-ghost.join-item.text-base-content` pattern as navi buttons\n- NO custom font sizes, NO custom colors — inherits from theme\n\n#### 2. Wire search button click in qbe-plugin.js\n- In the `isSelect` branch, find the `.qbe-search` button sibling and bind click\n- On click: call `openQbeModal($el, state)`\n- Reuse existing `loadSelectData` for initial combo population (already works)\n\n#### 3. Build QBE modal with datagrid (qbe-plugin.js)\n- Create modal dynamically via `$.modal.new()` or build DOM matching `+modal` output structure\n- Actually: build a hidden `<dialog>` element matching DUI modal mixin output (`.modal > .modal-box > h3 + content + .modal-action`)\n- Use DaisyUI modal classes only: `.modal`, `.modal-box`, `.modal-action`\n- Title from qbedef field label or "Search"\n- Content: a `<table>` element that gets `.datagrid()` initialized\n- Datagrid columns mapped from `state.options.fields`\n- queryParams from `state.options.queryParams` with `_dgrid:\'y\'`\n\n#### 4. Datagrid row select → combobox select → modal close\n- `onClickRow: function(idx, row)` on the datagrid\n- Extract value from `row[valueField]`\n- Call `$el.combobox(\'select\', value)` — this triggers onSelect → formLoad cascade\n- Call qbedef\'s `onSelect(row)` if defined\n- Close modal via `.modal(\'close\')`\n\n#### 5. Polish and verify\n- Screenshot every state: initial render, button hover, modal open, row selection\n- Verify button aligns perfectly with navi buttons (same height, same spacing)\n- Verify modal is properly themed (no custom colors/fonts)\n- Verify datagrid loads and displays data correctly\n- Verify row selection populates combo and closes modal\n- Test on sa_parts Part ID field (has qbe + navi)\n\n### Key decisions\n- Search button uses lucide `search` icon — consistent with rest of DUI\n- Modal is created once per qbe field (cached), not recreated on each click\n- Datagrid inside modal uses standard datagrid plugin — same as any other datagrid\n- No custom CSS. All DaisyUI + Tailwind utilities only.\n- `qbe` class on `<select>` is the detection mechanism (already preserved through mixin chain)'}
