2026-02-26 16:34:11,271 2290317 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 7, 'text': 'Root cause identified: in DUI Gate Pass JS, form load events trigger `$.page.hook("afterLoad", data)` (html/dui/mod/inv/js/inv_gpass.js:312,324), but no `afterLoad` hook is registered. The page defines `$.page.fn.loadData` (line 4) instead of registering hooks via `$.page.register({ hooks: { afterLoad: ... } })`. Per page-plugin behavior (public/dui/js/plugins/page-plugin.js:83-94), missing after-hook is a no-op, so `#gplines` never executes `datagrid(\'load\', {_sqlid:\'inv^gplines\', GP_ID:...})` (inv_gpass.js:5). Datagrid init guard returns false when GP_ID absent (inv_gpass.js:216-218), so initial auto-load is also canceled. Net effect: no inv^gplines request emitted from UI path, lines grid remains empty. Backend confirmed healthy: direct read-only probe `inv^gplines get` for GP-0005-18 returns 200 with 1 row (LINE_NO 1 DOC_ID SOSTT00000060.10). Migration manifest confirms regression source: scripts/migrator/mod/inv/inv_gpass.yaml records auto-rewrite of `dwap.page.loadData()` calls to `$.page.hook(\'afterLoad\', ...)` (lines 50-51) and `dwap.page.loadData -> $.page.fn.loadData` (line 52) without hook registration.'}
