2026-02-26 22:37:46,066 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'name': 'qbe', 'text': "## QBE Plugin — Full Implementation\n\n### ABSOLUTE RULE — SERVER-RENDERED FIRST\n- **EVERYTHING that CAN be done via pug mixins MUST be done via pug mixins**\n- **JS is ONLY for things that CANNOT be done server-side** (dynamic column config, event wiring, open/close)\n- This is the entire point of DUI — server-rendered mixins, not JS-built DOM\n- NEVER build modal structure, layout, containers, or any static HTML in JavaScript\n- If you catch yourself writing `$('<div>')` or `$('<dialog>')` or any HTML string in JS — STOP. It belongs in a mixin.\n\n### What QBE is\n- A combobox + modal datagrid for value selection\n- All combobox API methods are identical (getValue, setValue, onSelect, etc.)\n- The `<select>` is the visible field showing the selected value\n- Instead of picking from a native dropdown, user gets a modal with a full datagrid\n- Datagrid columns come from `qbedef.fields`, each with editors for filtering\n- User filters by columns, selects a row, that row's value populates the combobox\n\n### Key differences from plain combobox\n1. **Big data** — can't eagerly load all options, needs server-side filtering with pagination (`_dgrid:'y'`, `_rows`, `_page`)\n2. **Selection via modal** — modal opened via JS, but modal STRUCTURE is server-rendered\n3. **Filterable columns** — qbedef fields have editors so user can filter/search by any column\n4. **Row selection** — user picks a row, value populates the combobox, modal closes\n\n### Phase 1 requirements\n1. Add a search icon button to the qbe combobox (alongside existing navi buttons) — **server-rendered in input.pug** ✓ DONE\n2. QBE modal structure — **server-rendered via `+qbemodal` pug mixin** using `+modal`, `+vsplit`, `+datagrid`\n3. Datagrid columns/fields from qbedef definition — **JS only** (dynamic per field)\n4. Filter form fields from qbedef — **JS only** (dynamic per field)\n5. Data loaded from qbedef's `_sqlid` with `_dgrid:'y'` — **JS only**\n6. Row select → combobox select → modal close — **JS only**\n7. Event wiring (filter onChange, row click) — **JS only**\n\n### What is server-rendered (pug mixin)\n- Modal shell (`+modal`)\n- Vsplit layout (`+vsplit('320px')`)\n- Left filter panel container (empty, JS populates fields)\n- Right datagrid container (`+datagrid` with templates, no columns — JS adds columns)\n- ALL of the above is STATIC and IDENTICAL for every QBE field\n\n### What is JS only\n- Datagrid column configuration from qbedef\n- Filter form field creation from qbedef (these vary per field)\n- Event wiring (filter → reload, row click → select)\n- Opening/closing the modal\n- Row selection → combobox value population\n\n### Design rules — ABSOLUTE\n- Use `+modal()`, `+datagrid()` and existing DUI mixins — no raw HTML generation\n- JS ONLY when it CANNOT be done via mixins\n- All styling via DaisyUI/Tailwind utility classes — no inline fontSize, color, background overrides\n- No hardcoded hex colors or pixel font sizes — everything follows the theme\n- Zero custom CSS. If a mixin doesn't support something, extend the mixin — don't bypass it"}
2026-02-26 22:39:03,422 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'name': 'qbe', 'text': '## Phase 1 Implementation Plan (CORRECTED)\n\n### ABSOLUTE RULE: Server-rendered first, JS only when impossible via mixins\n\n### Architecture\n- A `+qbemodal` pug mixin renders the STATIC modal structure (identical for every QBE field)\n- qbe-plugin.js ONLY handles dynamic parts: columns, filter fields, events, open/close\n- NO raw HTML generation in JS. NONE. EVER.\n\n### What is server-rendered (`+qbemodal` pug mixin)\n- `+modal` shell (dialog.modal > .modal-box)\n- `+vsplit(\'320px\')` layout inside the modal\n- Left panel: empty container div for filter fields (JS populates from qbedef)\n- Right panel: `+datagrid` with column templates but NO columns (JS adds from qbedef)\n- This mixin is included ONCE in the page layout — shared by all QBE fields on the page\n\n### What is JS only (qbe-plugin.js)\n- Find the server-rendered `#qbe-modal` element\n- Configure datagrid columns from qbedef definition\n- Build filter form fields from qbedef (these vary per field — cannot be server-rendered)\n- Wire filter field onChange → datagrid reload with filter params\n- Wire row click → combobox select → modal close\n- Open/close the modal\n\n### Steps\n\n#### 1. ✓ DONE — Search icon button in input.pug\n\n#### 2. ✓ DONE — Column templates in datagrid mixin\n\n#### 3. Create `+qbemodal` pug mixin (SERVER-SIDE)\n- New mixin in input.pug (or separate file)\n- Renders: `+modal(title="Search")#qbe-modal` > `+vsplit(\'320px\')` > left `.qbe-filters` container + right `+datagrid`\n- Include in page layout so it\'s available to all QBE fields\n- Delete the entire `openQbeModal` JS function\n\n#### 4. Rewrite JS to use server-rendered modal\n- `openQbeModal($el, state)` becomes: find `#qbe-modal`, configure datagrid columns, populate filter fields, open modal\n- Filter fields built from qbedef (JS — dynamic per field)\n- Datagrid columns from qbedef (JS — dynamic per field)\n- onClickRow → combobox select → modal close\n\n#### 5. Visual polish and screenshot verification'}
