2026-02-26 22:54:08,977 2119379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 3, 'id': 482, 'text': '## Step 3: QBE Modal — SERVER-RENDERED + JS wiring\n\n### RULE: Server-rendered first. JS ONLY when it cannot be done via mixins.\n\n### Server-rendered: `+qbemodal` pug mixin\nCreate a pug mixin that renders the STATIC modal structure. It is identical for every QBE field.\n- `+modal(title="Search")#qbe-modal` — modal shell\n- Inside: `+vsplit(\'320px\')` — split layout\n- Left panel: empty `div.qbe-filters` container (JS populates filter fields from qbedef)\n- Right panel: `+datagrid` with column templates but NO columns (JS adds columns from qbedef)\n- Rendered ONCE per page, shared by all QBE fields\n- NO raw HTML in JS for any of this. It is a pug mixin.\n\n### JS only: qbe-plugin.js `openQbeModal($el, state)`\n- Find server-rendered `#qbe-modal`\n- Configure datagrid columns from `state.options.fields` (dynamic — varies per qbedef)\n- Create filter form fields from qbedef editors (dynamic — varies per qbedef)\n- Wire filter onChange → datagrid reload with filter params\n- Wire onClickRow → combobox select → modal close\n- Open the modal\n\n### What was deleted\n- `openQbeModal()` (~90 lines) that built the entire modal in JS — DELETED\n- `loadModalData()` (~50 lines) that manually built table rows in JS — DELETED\n- Search button click handler stubbed with TODO\n\n### Status\n- Pug mixin not yet created\n- JS wiring not yet written'}
