2026-02-26 23:10:00,699 2334379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': '## QBE Plugin — Full Implementation\n\n### ABSOLUTE RULE — SERVER-RENDERED FIRST\n- **EVERYTHING that CAN be done via pug mixins MUST be done via pug mixins**\n- **JS is ONLY for event wiring** — open/close modal, row click → select, filter change → reload\n- NEVER build static HTML structures in JavaScript — no `$(\'<div>\')`, no HTML strings, no DOM construction\n- Use existing APIs (datagrid plugin for data loading, combobox plugin for value selection) — do NOT rewrite them\n- If a structure is STATIC and IDENTICAL every time → it belongs in a pug mixin, period\n\n### What QBE is\n- A combobox + modal datagrid for value selection\n- All combobox API methods are identical (getValue, setValue, onSelect, etc.)\n- The `<select>` is the visible field showing the selected value\n- Instead of picking from a native dropdown, user gets a modal with a full datagrid\n- Datagrid columns come from `qbedef.fields`, each with editors for filtering\n- User filters by columns, selects a row, that row\'s value populates the combobox\n\n### Key differences from plain combobox\n1. **Big data** — can\'t eagerly load all options, needs server-side filtering with pagination (`_dgrid:\'y\'`, `_rows`, `_page`)\n2. **Selection via modal** — modal opened via JS, but modal STRUCTURE is server-rendered\n3. **Filterable columns** — qbedef fields have editors so user can filter/search by any column\n4. **Row selection** — user picks a row, value populates the combobox, modal closes\n\n### What is server-rendered (pug mixins — ALL of these)\n- `+modal` — dialog shell, id="qbe-modal", title="Search", no-form, max-w="4xl"\n- `+vsplit(\'280px\')` — two-column layout (filter panel left, results right)\n- `+datagrid` — right panel, no JSON config, empty columns (JS configures from qbedef)\n- `+modal-footer` — action bar with Cancel\n- `+button` — Search button in footer\n- Filter fields use `#dui-fitem-tpl` template (already in +modal) cloned via fitem API\n- **Zero non-mixin elements. Zero raw HTML in JS. Zero custom divs.**\n\n### What is JS only (event wiring ONLY)\n- Search button click → open modal (`dialog.showModal()`)\n- Row click → combobox select → close modal\n- Filter change → datagrid reload\n- Configure datagrid columns from qbedef (dynamic per field)\n- Build filter fields by cloning fitem template (dynamic per field)\n- All data loading uses EXISTING APIs (datagrid plugin, combobox plugin) — no custom ajax\n\n### Design rules — ABSOLUTE\n- Use `+modal()`, `+vsplit()`, `+datagrid()`, `+modal-footer`, `+button` and existing DUI mixins\n- JS ONLY for event wiring — never for structure, layout, or data loading\n- All styling via DaisyUI/Tailwind utility classes — no inline styles\n- No hardcoded hex colors or pixel font sizes\n- Zero custom CSS. Zero raw HTML generation in JS.'}
2026-02-26 23:10:13,978 2334379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Phase 1 Implementation Plan (CORRECTED v2)\n\n### ABSOLUTE RULE: Server-rendered first. JS = event wiring ONLY.\n\n### Architecture\n- `+qbemodal` pug mixin renders the ENTIRE static modal structure using ONLY existing mixins\n- qbe-plugin.js handles ONLY: event wiring, dynamic column config, dynamic filter field creation (via fitem API)\n- All data loading uses EXISTING plugin APIs (datagrid, combobox) — no custom ajax\n- NO raw HTML generation in JS. NONE. EVER.\n\n### Server-rendered: `+qbemodal` pug mixin (ALL mixins)\n1. `+modal` — dialog shell (id="qbe-modal", title="Search", no-form, max-w="4xl")\n2. `+vsplit(\'280px\')` — two-column layout inside modal\n3. Left panel: block content of vsplit (JS appends fitem-structured fields via `#dui-fitem-tpl`)\n4. Right panel: `+datagrid` — no JSON config, empty columns, JS configures from qbedef\n5. `+modal-footer` — action bar\n6. `+button` — "Search" button inside footer\n- Zero non-mixin elements. Zero custom divs.\n\n### JS only: event wiring (qbe-plugin.js)\n- Search button click → `dialog.showModal()`\n- Configure datagrid columns from qbedef fields (dynamic per field)\n- Build filter fields by cloning `#dui-fitem-tpl` (dynamic per field)\n- Filter change → datagrid reload (uses existing datagrid API)\n- Row click → combobox select → close modal (uses existing combobox API)\n\n### Steps\n\n#### 1. ✓ DONE — Search icon button in input.pug\n\n#### 2. ✓ DONE — Column templates in datagrid mixin\n\n#### 3. Create `+qbemodal` pug mixin + include in layout\n- Composes: +modal > +vsplit > +datagrid + +modal-footer > +button\n- Add to input.pug (alongside +qbe)\n- Include once in layout.pug\n- Server restart required (pug change)\n\n#### 4. Wire JS event handlers in qbe-plugin.js\n- Search button click → open modal\n- Configure datagrid columns from qbedef\n- Clone fitem template for filter fields\n- Filter onChange → datagrid reload\n- Row click → combobox setValue → close modal\n- Use existing datagrid/combobox plugin APIs for all data operations\n\n#### 5. Visual polish and screenshot verification'}
2026-02-26 23:10:25,088 2334379 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 3, 'id': 482, 'text': '## Step 3: QBE Modal — ALL mixins, JS = event wiring only\n\n### Server-rendered: `+qbemodal` pug mixin\nComposes ONLY existing mixins — zero custom elements:\n1. `+modal(title="Search" no-form)#qbe-modal(max-w="4xl")` — dialog shell\n2. `+vsplit(\'280px\')` — two-column grid (filters left, results right)\n3. Left panel: receives filter fields via `#dui-fitem-tpl` clone (JS, dynamic per qbedef)\n4. Right panel: `+datagrid` — no JSON config, empty columns, JS configures from qbedef\n5. `+modal-footer` — action bar with Cancel\n6. `+button("Search")` — inside footer, triggers query\n\n### Location\n- Mixin added to `input.pug` (alongside `+qbe`)\n- Called once in `layout.pug` so it\'s available on every page\n\n### JS changes (qbe-plugin.js)\n- Wire search button click → find `#qbe-modal`, open via `dialog.showModal()`\n- Configure datagrid columns from qbedef (existing datagrid API)\n- Clone `#dui-fitem-tpl` for filter fields (existing fitem pattern)\n- Filter onChange → datagrid reload (existing datagrid API)\n- Row click → combobox setValue → close modal (existing combobox API)\n- NO custom ajax, NO raw HTML, NO custom CSS\n\n### What was deleted previously\n- `openQbeModal()` (~90 lines raw HTML) — DELETED\n- `loadModalData()` (~50 lines raw table rows) — DELETED\n- Search button click handler stubbed with TODO'}
