2026-02-27 09:16:59,976 2388117 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Identify the exact runtime cause of the Gate Pass lines datagrid (#gplines) showing no data after a Gate Pass record is navigated to, and define the minimum-risk code fix. No code changes in this task.'}
2026-02-27 09:17:22,756 2388117 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Root Cause (confirmed by code trace)\n\n### PRIMARY BUG — `$.page.fn.loadData` is never called\n\n**Data load call chain in `inv_gpass.js` (current):**\n1. User selects a Gate Pass ID → form `#gphead` loads head data via AJAX\n2. `form-plugin.js` fires `$form.trigger(\'loadDone\', [data])` then `$.page.hook(\'afterLoad\', data)`\n3. `inv_gpass.js` `loadDone` handler runs: `$.page.hook("afterLoad", data)`\n4. `$.page.hook("afterLoad", data)` looks up `hooks[\'afterLoad\']` — **this is empty, so it is a complete no-op**\n5. `$.page.fn.loadData` is defined on `$.page.fn` (a separate plain object), NOT in `hooks` — it is never called\n6. Therefore `$(\'#gplines\').datagrid(\'load\', {..., GP_ID: data.GP_ID})` is **never executed**\n7. The lines datagrid never receives `GP_ID` and never fetches rows → empty table\n\n**Original code (inv_gpass.js.1 backup — worked):**\n- Stored function as `$.dui.page.loadData = function(data){...}`\n- `loadDone` handler called `$.dui.page.loadData(data)` directly\n\n**Migration introduced break:**\n- Changed storage to `$.page.fn.loadData = function(data){...}`\n- Changed call to `$.page.hook("afterLoad", data)` (hook dispatch)\n- But `$.page.fn.loadData` was NEVER registered into `hooks[\'afterLoad\']`\n- `page-plugin.js::hook()` only dispatches from the private `hooks` var, not from `$.page.fn`\n\n**Also broken in `done` handler** (same issue + typo):\n- `$.page.hook("afterLoad", data)` — same no-op\n- `$(\'#GP_ID\').texbox(\'getValue\')` — typo: `texbox` should be `textbox`\n\n### SECONDARY GAP — `loadFilter` never applied\n- `$.page.fn.opts.loadFilter` is defined in page JS but `requestData()` in datagrid-plugin.js never calls `opts.loadFilter`\n- If the server returns a null/empty response, the loadFilter normalization is bypassed\n- Lower priority — if the primary fix works, standard `{rows:[], total:0}` responses will render fine\n\n## Fix Path (do not implement here)\n\n**Minimal fix in `html/dui/mod/inv/js/inv_gpass.js`:**\n\nIn the `loadDone` handler, replace:\n```js$.page.hook("afterLoad", data);```\nwith:\n```js$.page.fn.loadData(data);```\n\nSame change in the `done` handler, and also fix the `texbox` typo.\n\n**Alternative fix (more invasive):**\nAfter defining `$.page.fn.loadData`, register it as the `afterLoad` hook:\n```js$.page.register({ hooks: { afterLoad: function(data){ $.page.fn.loadData(data); } } });\n```\nThis would work because `form-plugin.js` itself already calls `$.page.hook(\'afterLoad\', data)` after each form load, so no change to the event handlers is needed.\n\n## Validation Checklist (after fix)\n1. Navigate to an existing Gate Pass — lines datagrid populates with rows\n2. Navigate to a new (add) Gate Pass — lines datagrid is empty (expected)\n3. Save a new Gate Pass head — lines datagrid add button becomes enabled\n4. Delete a Gate Pass — lines datagrid clears'}
