2026-02-27 10:20:16,882 1420 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'id': 424, 'text': "Root causes confirmed via code trace (inv_gpass.js + datagrid-plugin.js + datagrid.pug):\n\nRC-1: Wrong modal selector — inv_gpass.js:23-24 uses `$('#_dgform > form input[textboxname=DOC_TYPE')` which references a non-existent EUI element. DUI modal ID is `gplines_editor`; inputs use `name` not `textboxname`. Both dgDocType and qbeDocId are always empty jQuery objects → all subsequent combobox/qbe init silently no-ops.\n\nRC-2: DOC_TYPE combobox rendered with no data — datagrid.gplines.json editor options for DOC_TYPE have no `data` array. The Pug mixin only emits data-options when eo.data exists (datagrid.pug:129). Combobox opens empty. The dynamic fix via loadData() never fires (RC-1).\n\nRC-3: DOC_TYPE onSelect handler never attached — dgDocType.combobox({onSelect:...}) at inv_gpass.js:27-48 also no-ops because dgDocType is empty. Selecting a DOC_TYPE value cannot enable DOC_ID or set the qbe _sqlid endpoint.\n\nRC-4: DOC_ID qbe stays permanently readonly — The JS column def sets readonly:true as initial state, intending the onSelect handler to toggle it. Since RC-1 breaks the handler wire-up, DOC_ID is locked readonly forever in the modal.\n\nRC-5: loadData() gated on GP_ID — form#gphead.on('loadDone') at inv_gpass.js:311 returns early if !data.GP_ID, so even the (broken) initialisation never runs for new GP records.\n\nFix plan:\n1. Fix selectors in loadData() — use `#gplines_editor [name=DOC_TYPE]` and `#gplines_editor [name=DOC_ID]`.\n2. Move DOC_TYPE combobox init (loadData + onSelect) to fire when the Add modal opens (datagrid Add button click or a modal open event), not only on form loadDone.\n3. Ensure onSelect for DOC_TYPE correctly toggles DOC_ID readonly and sets qbe _sqlid before opening the search panel.\n4. Verify Edit flow (populateEditor + correct selector) also honours DOC_TYPE-driven DOC_ID state."}
2026-02-27 10:20:30,559 1420 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Fix modal selectors in inv_gpass.js loadData()', 'description': "Replace the two broken EUI selectors in loadData() (lines 23-24 of inv_gpass.js):\n\nFROM:\n  `$('#_dgform > form input[textboxname=DOC_TYPE')`\n  `$('#_dgform > form input[textboxname=DOC_ID')`\n\nTO:\n  `$('#gplines_editor [name=DOC_TYPE]')`\n  `$('#gplines_editor [name=DOC_ID]')`\n\n`#_dgform` does not exist in the DUI page. The actual editor modal ID is `gplines_editor` (set by datagrid.pug line 110: `id=dgId + '_editor'`). DUI inputs use the `name` attribute, not `textboxname` (an EUI convention). These two lines being wrong is RC-1 — the root of all four cascading failures."}
2026-02-27 10:20:39,793 1420 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Move DOC_TYPE/DOC_ID modal init from loadData() to Add-button open event', 'description': 'The DOC_TYPE data-load + onSelect wire-up currently sits inside `$.page.fn.loadData()`, which is only called when an existing GP record is loaded (gated by `if(!data.GP_ID) return` at line 311).\n\nFor new GP records, `loadData()` never fires → DOC_TYPE combobox has no options and onSelect is never attached.\n\nRectification: Extract the DOC_TYPE combobox init block (currently lines 16-48) into a named helper function `initLineEditor()`. Call it:\n  a) From `loadData()` as before (for existing GP records), AND\n  b) From the Add button click handler, immediately before `state._editor.showModal()` is called.\n\nThe Add button handler in datagrid-plugin.js calls `populateEditor(state._editor, null)` then `state._editor.showModal()`. Since inv_gpass.js owns the page logic, hook into the Add button click by listening on `#gplines_add` click (after datagrid init at line 284) and calling `initLineEditor()` there.'}
2026-02-27 10:20:50,502 1420 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Ensure DOC_TYPE onSelect correctly enables DOC_ID and sets qbe endpoint', 'description': "Once selectors are fixed (step 5) and initLineEditor() runs at modal-open time (step 6), verify the onSelect handler logic is correct for both Add and Edit flows:\n\n- When DOC_TYPE = 'NIL': DOC_ID must be set readonly and not required.\n- When DOC_TYPE = 'SO': DOC_ID must become editable, required, and qbe _sqlid set to `sales^sor_qbe` with CUST_ID from #GP_TYPE_ID.\n- When DOC_TYPE = 'WO': DOC_ID must become editable, required, and qbe _sqlid set to `inv^gp_opnrefs_qbe` (CUST_ID removed from params).\n\nThe onSelect handler currently references `qbeDocId.qbe('options').dlog.dg.datagrid('reload')` — verify this qbe API path works against the DUI qbe plugin (not EUI's qbe). If the qbe plugin API differs, adjust the reload call accordingly.\n\nNo change needed if the logic is confirmed correct after selector fix."}
2026-02-27 10:20:55,163 487 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Add locked:true/false to migrator — hard lock with --lock/--unlock CLI', 'description': 'Add `locked: true/false` field to migrator YAML root. Behavior:\n\n**Migration runtime (FIRST CHECK):**\n- Before reading pug, includes, or JS — check YAML for `locked: true`\n- If locked, abort immediately for that page and ALL associated files (includes, JS)\n- Output: `LOCKED: inv^sa_parts — skipped (owner: PAC)`\n- This is the very first check in the pipeline, before any file I/O\n\n**CLI commands:**\n- `--lock inv^sa_parts` — sets `locked: true` in YAML, only if caller matches `user` field\n- `--unlock inv^sa_parts` — sets `locked: false`, same owner check\n- No `user` field set → cannot lock (must claim ownership first)\n- Non-owner attempting lock/unlock → error: `Cannot lock/unlock inv^sa_parts — owned by X`\n\n**Cascade:** locked page = locked includes + locked JS. One flag protects everything.'}
2026-02-27 10:20:57,407 1420 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Verify Edit flow: populateEditor restores DOC_TYPE selection and DOC_ID state', 'description': "When the user double-clicks an existing line (Edit flow), `populateEditor(state._editor, row)` sets raw input values from the row data. After this:\n\n1. DOC_TYPE combobox must show the correct option (SO/WO/NIL). Since `populateEditor` sets `inp.value` directly (bypassing combobox widget API), check whether the combobox plugin reads the underlying input value on open or requires `combobox('setValue', val)` to render the label correctly.\n\n2. DOC_ID readonly state must reflect the restored DOC_TYPE:\n   - If DOC_TYPE restored to NIL → DOC_ID should remain readonly.\n   - If DOC_TYPE restored to SO/WO → DOC_ID should be editable.\n\nIf `populateEditor` raw value assignment is insufficient for the combobox widget, add a post-populate step in inv_gpass.js that calls `combobox('setValue')` and triggers the onSelect logic to restore DOC_ID state.\n\nThis step is verify-only unless a defect is found; document the outcome either way."}
