2026-02-27 16:16:26,257 14085 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'id': 451, 'text': "## Key Decisions from Discussion\n\n### Three categories of EUI code in migrated pages:\n1. **Dead code** — page doing things plugins now manage (button state, form lifecycle). Remove it.\n2. **Renamed APIs** — same function exists in DUI under different name. Translate it.\n3. **Missing equivalents** — EUI pattern with no DUI equivalent. Flag for decision.\n\n### Translation map actions:\n- **translate** — direct DUI replacement exists, swap the call\n- **alias** — shim exists, works for now, mark for cleanup\n- **deprecated** — plugin manages globally, remove from page\n- **missing** — no DUI equivalent, needs building or rethinking\n\n### Translation map is ADDITIVE:\n- Do NOT scan all 105+ pages upfront — start with known entries from inv_gpass\n- Each time the skill runs on a new page, any new pattern encountered gets added to the YAML\n- The map grows organically as pages get fixed\n- The skill both CONSUMES and UPDATES the map in a single run:\n  - Read docs/dui/migration-map.yaml at start of run\n  - For each call in the page JS, check the map\n  - Found → apply the action (translate/remove/leave alias)\n  - Not found → follow lookup procedure: check docs/dui/*.md, check plugins for shims, classify it, add it to the YAML, then apply\n\n### Critical rules learned:\n- Pages NEVER control buttons — not datagrid toolbar, not main toolbar, not butEn()\n- Form plugin manages button state via state machine\n- Datagrid plugin manages its own add/edit/del buttons\n- loadData (loading datagrid on record select) is the one critical page-specific function\n- $.page.hook('afterLoad', ...) requires $.page.register({ hooks: { afterLoad: fn }})\n- The migrator converts call-sites but doesn't add registration — this is a known gap\n\n### Skill procedure (9 steps):\n1. Build/update translation map from EUI patterns found\n2. Open page in EUI, load record, observe full behaviour\n3. Open same page in DUI, same record, observe what happens\n4. Diff the behaviour — missing, broken, interfering\n5. Read page JS, classify every call against translation map\n6. Apply fixes — strip deprecated, translate renamed, wire missing\n7. Test full lifecycle — load, add, edit, save, delete, navigate\n8. Compare with EUI — confirm DUI matches\n9. Record findings — update migration YAML\n\n### Files:\n- Translation map: docs/dui/migration-map.yaml\n- Skill: /root/.claude/skills/fix-migrated-page/SKILL.md"}
