2026-02-27 16:17:37,622 14085 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': "## Skill Procedure (9 steps)\n\n1. Read `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml` to load known patterns\n2. Open page in EUI (legacy), select a record, observe: field population, datagrid loading, button states, full behaviour\n3. Open same page in DUI, same record, observe what actually happens\n4. Diff behaviour — what's missing, broken, or interfering\n5. Read page JS, classify every call against the map:\n   - Found → apply action (translate / remove / leave alias)\n   - Not found → lookup: check `docs/dui/*.md` first, then `public/dui/js/plugins/` for shims, classify, add to YAML\n6. Apply fixes — remove deprecated code, translate renamed APIs, wire missing connections\n7. Test full lifecycle — load record, add new, edit, save, delete, navigate between records\n8. Compare with EUI — same record, confirm DUI now matches\n9. Update `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml` with any new patterns found, update page's migration YAML\n\n## Classification Rules\n\nEvery EUI API call in a page script gets one of four actions:\n\n| Action | Meaning | What to do |\n|---|---|---|\n| translate | Direct DUI equivalent exists | Replace the call |\n| alias | Shim exists via `$.dui.shim()` | Leave for now, works. Mark for eventual cleanup |\n| deprecated | Plugin manages this globally | Remove from page entirely |\n| missing | No DUI equivalent | Stop and ask user. Build equivalent, create shim, or rethink logic |\n\n## Translation Map Rules\n\n- Map is **additive** — seeded from inv_gpass, grows as each page is fixed\n- Do NOT scan all 105+ pages upfront\n- The skill both **consumes and updates** the map in a single run\n- All shims MUST be registered via `$.dui.shim()` — no random global aliases\n- The YAML is the single source of truth for what shims exist and where\n- Each entry has: `match`, `action`, `shim` (exists/name/registered_in), `dui`, `see_also`, `managed_by` (if deprecated), `notes`\n\n## Absolute Rules\n\n- Pages NEVER control buttons — not datagrid toolbar, not main toolbar, not butEn()\n- `loadData` is the one critical page-specific function — loads datagrid(s) when a record is selected\n- `$.page.hook('afterLoad')` requires `$.page.register({ hooks: { afterLoad: fn } })` — the migrator does NOT add this registration (known gap)\n\n## Files\n\n- Translation map: `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml`\n- Skill: `/root/.claude/skills/fix-migrated-page/SKILL.md`"}
2026-02-27 16:18:01,193 14085 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'id': 452, 'text': '## Translation Map Seed Data\n\nCopy this YAML block directly into `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml` as the initial content.\n\nWhen encountering an unknown EUI call not in this map:\n1. Check `docs/dui/*.md` for the DUI equivalent\n2. Check `public/dui/js/plugins/` for existing shims (`grep dui.shim`)\n3. If not found, classify as `missing` and add to this file\n4. If a shim is needed, register it via `$.dui.shim()` in the correct plugin and record here\n\n```yaml\npatterns:\n  ajaxget:\n    match: "ajaxget("\n    action: alias\n    shim: { exists: true, name: ajaxget, registered_in: ajax-plugin.js }\n    dui: "$.dui.ajax()"\n    see_also: docs/dui/ajax.md\n    notes: "shim via $.dui.shim, deprecated"\n\n  clone:\n    match: "clone("\n    action: alias\n    shim: { exists: true, name: clone, registered_in: utils.js }\n    dui: null\n    notes: "window.clone in utils.js, works as-is"\n\n  loadpage:\n    match: "loadpage("\n    action: alias\n    shim: { exists: true, name: loadpage, registered_in: nav-plugin.js }\n    dui: null\n    notes: "shim exists, deprecated warning"\n\n  isronly:\n    match: "isronly("\n    action: alias\n    shim: { exists: true, name: isronly, registered_in: form-plugin.js }\n    dui: null\n    notes: "shim exists, deprecated warning"\n\n  getapp:\n    match: "getapp("\n    action: alias\n    shim: { exists: true, name: getapp, registered_in: page-plugin.js }\n    dui: null\n    notes: "shim exists, deprecated warning"\n\n  tbar_dgre:\n    match: ".tbar.dgre_"\n    action: deprecated\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    managed_by: datagrid-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/datagrid.md\n    notes: "_sink Proxy absorbs silently. Dead code. Remove."\n\n  linkbutton_enable:\n    match: ".linkbutton(\'enable\')"\n    action: deprecated\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    managed_by: toolbar-plugin / datagrid-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/button.md\n    notes: "Plugins manage button state. Remove."\n\n  linkbutton_disable:\n    match: ".linkbutton(\'disable\')"\n    action: deprecated\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    managed_by: toolbar-plugin / datagrid-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/button.md\n    notes: "Same as linkbutton_enable."\n\n  butEn:\n    match: "butEn("\n    action: deprecated\n    shim: { exists: true, name: butEn, registered_in: toolbar-plugin.js }\n    managed_by: form-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/toolbar.md\n    notes: "Shim exists but gated by form state machine. Remove from pages."\n\n  _dgform_selector:\n    match: "#_dgform"\n    action: translate\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    dui: "#<dgId>_editor"\n    see_also: docs/dui/datagrid.md\n    notes: "Replace with datagrid ID + _editor suffix."\n\n  textboxname:\n    match: "textboxname="\n    action: translate\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    dui: "name="\n    notes: "EUI attr → standard name attr."\n\n  columns_inline:\n    match: "columns:[["\n    action: translate\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    dui: "datagrid.<id>.json"\n    see_also: docs/dui/datagrid.md\n    notes: "Move to JSON config file."\n\n  rowEditor:\n    match: ".rowEditor("\n    action: deprecated\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    managed_by: datagrid-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/datagrid.md\n    notes: "DUI uses JSON config + editor modal. Remove."\n\n  editButs:\n    match: ".datagrid(\'editButs\')"\n    action: deprecated\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    managed_by: datagrid-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/datagrid.md\n    notes: "DUI uses asdpx. Remove."\n\n  dwap_page_loadData_def:\n    match: "$.page.fn.loadData ="\n    action: translate\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    dui: "$.page.register({ hooks: { afterLoad: fn } })"\n    notes: "Migrator misses this. Must register as hook."\n```'}
2026-02-27 16:18:11,736 14085 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'id': 453, 'text': "## DUI Plugin Ownership — What Pages Must NOT Touch\n\n### form-plugin.js\n- Owns: #but_add, #but_save, #but_del, #but_cancel\n- State machine: idle → loading → view → edit → saving\n- Intercepts page butEn() calls when state machine is active\n- Events: loadDone, done, changed, success\n- asdpx attr controls which buttons appear (a=add, s=save, d=delete, x=cancel)\n\n### datagrid-plugin.js\n- Owns: #<dgId>_add, #<dgId>_edit, #<dgId>_del (plain buttons, NOT linkbuttons)\n- tbarEnable()/tbarDisable() toggle CSS: opacity-40 pointer-events-none\n- opts.tbar = Proxy (_sink) — absorbs EUI tbar.dgre_ calls silently\n- Column defs belong in datagrid.<id>.json, not inline JS\n- Editor modal managed by plugin\n\n### toolbar-plugin.js\n- Renders .tbut buttons from pug\n- butEn(mask) enables/disables by asdpx character mask\n- Gates page butEn() calls when form state machine is active\n\n### linkbutton-plugin.js\n- .linkbutton('enable'/'disable') for .tbut checks $.dui.asdpx\n- Non-tbut: toggles disabled attr + opacity classes\n- Datagrid buttons are NOT linkbutton-initialized\n\n### page-plugin.js\n- $.page.ready(fn) — invokes immediately (DOM already available)\n- $.page.fn — page-specific function namespace\n- $.page.register({ hooks, fn }) — registers hooks and functions\n- $.page.hook(name, ...args) — invokes from PRIVATE registry\n- afterLoad hook = how pages trigger datagrid loading on record select\n\n### ajax-plugin.js\n- $.dui.ajax() — proper DUI ajax\n- window.ajaxget shim via dui.shim() — deprecated but functional"}
