2026-02-27 16:27:55,783 14085 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'id': 450, 'kind': 'goal', 'text': '## Purpose\n\nDeliver a fully working DUI page that behaves identically to its EUI counterpart. Not "translated code" — a working page. If the user can tell the difference between EUI and DUI behaviour, you are not done.\n\nThe skill is a systematic method to achieve this. The translation map is a growing knowledge base that makes each page faster. But the success criteria is always: **does the page work?**\n\n## Deliverables\n\n1. `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml` — EUI→DUI translation map (additive, grows with each page fixed)\n2. `/root/.claude/skills/fix-migrated-page/SKILL.md` — step-by-step skill procedure\n3. Test both on inv_gpass (first real page fix, mid-flight in task `manual-sa-gpass`)\n\n## What This Is NOT\n\n- NOT a pattern-matching exercise — ticking off translated calls doesn\'t mean the page works\n- NOT a one-shot audit — it\'s an iterative fix loop: change → verify in browser → fix again\n- NOT complete until Playwright confirms the page matches EUI behaviour'}
2026-02-27 16:28:33,572 14085 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'id': 451, 'kind': 'plan', 'text': "## Purpose — Read This First\n\nThe goal is a **fully working page**. Not translated code, not a clean JS file — a page where every feature works identically to EUI. Pattern classification and code fixes are tools to get there, not the objective.\n\nPlaywright (browser automation) is used throughout — not as a final check but as the primary verification loop. Every fix is validated in the browser before moving on. Screenshots, console errors, network requests, and visual comparison with the EUI page are how you know if something works.\n\n## Skill Procedure\n\n### Phase 1: Establish Baseline\n\n1. **Read `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml`** to load known patterns\n2. **Open page in EUI** (legacy server via Playwright) — select a record, observe and screenshot:\n   - Field population, datagrid loading, button states, tab content\n   - Full user workflow: add, edit, save, delete, navigate\n   - This is your reference — DUI must match this\n3. **Open same page in DUI** (Playwright) — same record, observe and screenshot:\n   - What loads, what doesn't, console errors, network failures\n   - Compare side-by-side with EUI screenshots\n\n### Phase 2: Classify and Fix (iterative loop)\n\n4. **Read page JS**, classify every call against the map:\n   - **Known pattern** → apply the action immediately (translate / remove / leave alias)\n   - **Unknown pattern** → investigate:\n     1. Check `docs/dui/*.md` for DUI equivalent\n     2. Check `public/dui/js/plugins/` for existing shims (`grep dui.shim`)\n     3. Classify (translate / alias / deprecated / missing)\n     4. **Fix the issue** using the method you just determined\n     5. Add the new pattern to `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml`\n   - **Missing (no equivalent)** → STOP and ask the user\n5. **After each batch of fixes** — reload page in Playwright:\n   - Check console for errors\n   - Check network requests\n   - Take screenshot, compare with EUI baseline\n   - If something is still broken → fix and repeat\n   - Do NOT move on until the current fix is verified working\n\n### Phase 3: Full Lifecycle Test\n\n6. **Test every user action** in DUI via Playwright:\n   - Load a record (fkey select) — fields populate, datagrid loads\n   - Add new record — form clears, fields editable\n   - Edit existing — fields become editable, save works\n   - Delete — record removed, form clears\n   - Navigate between records — state resets correctly\n7. **Compare each action with EUI** — same record, same action, screenshot both\n   - If behaviour differs → investigate, fix, re-test\n\n### Phase 4: Record\n\n8. **Update `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml`** with any new patterns discovered\n9. **Update page's migrator YAML** (`scripts/migrator/mod/<module>/<page>.yaml`) status\n\n## Classification Rules\n\n| Action | Meaning | What to do |\n|---|---|---|\n| translate | Direct DUI equivalent exists | Replace the call |\n| alias | Shim exists via `$.dui.shim()` | Leave for now, works. Mark for eventual cleanup |\n| deprecated | Plugin manages this globally | Remove from page entirely |\n| missing | No DUI equivalent | Stop and ask user |\n\n## Translation Map Rules\n\n- Map is **additive** — seeded from inv_gpass, grows with each page\n- The skill both **consumes and updates** the map in a single run\n- All shims MUST be registered via `$.dui.shim()` — no random global aliases\n- The YAML is the single source of truth for what shims exist and where\n- Each entry has: `match`, `action`, `shim` (exists/name/registered_in), `dui`, `see_also`, `managed_by`, `notes`\n\n## Absolute Rules\n\n- Pages NEVER control buttons — not datagrid toolbar, not main toolbar, not butEn()\n- `loadData` is the one critical page-specific function — loads datagrid(s) on record select\n- `$.page.hook('afterLoad')` requires `$.page.register({ hooks: { afterLoad: fn } })` — migrator does NOT add this (known gap)\n- Screenshots go in `.pw/` directory\n- Browser viewport: 1600x900 minimum\n\n## Files\n\n- Translation map: `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml`\n- Skill: `/root/.claude/skills/fix-migrated-page/SKILL.md`\n- DUI login: `http://localhost:3333/?token=p4-agent-dev-token&ui=dui`\n- EUI login: use `/pure3d` skill for legacy server access"}
2026-02-27 16:30:34,408 14085 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'id': 451, 'kind': 'plan', 'text': "## Purpose — Read This First\n\nThe goal is a **fully working page**. Not translated code, not a clean JS file — a page where every feature works identically to EUI. Pattern classification and code fixes are tools to get there, not the objective.\n\nPlaywright (browser automation) is used throughout — not as a final check but as the primary verification loop. Every fix is validated in the browser before moving on. Screenshots, console errors, network requests, and visual comparison with the EUI page are how you know if something works.\n\n## Skill Procedure\n\n### Phase 1: Observe\n\n1. **Open DUI page in Playwright**, select a record\n2. **Collect symptoms** — do NOT touch any code yet:\n   - Console errors (TypeError, ReferenceError, etc.)\n   - Empty datagrids (check if network request was made)\n   - Fields not populating\n   - Buttons not responding or missing\n   - Network failures (404, 500, missing requests)\n   - Visual differences from expected layout\n   - Take screenshots of everything broken\n3. **Open same page in EUI** (legacy server via Playwright), same record — screenshot as baseline reference\n\n### Phase 2: Diagnose\n\n4. **Read `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml`** — cross-reference collected symptoms against the map\n   - Many console errors map directly to known patterns (e.g. `TypeError: ajaxget is not a function` → `ajaxget` entry)\n   - Known symptom with known fix → queue the fix\n   - Unknown symptom → proceed to code investigation\n5. **Read page JS**, classify any remaining unmatched calls against the map:\n   - **Known pattern** → apply the action (translate / remove / leave alias)\n   - **Unknown pattern** → investigate:\n     1. Check `docs/dui/*.md` for DUI equivalent\n     2. Check `public/dui/js/plugins/` for existing shims (`grep dui.shim`)\n     3. Classify (translate / alias / deprecated / missing)\n     4. Add the new pattern AND its symptom(s) to `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml`\n   - **Missing (no equivalent)** → STOP and ask the user\n\n### Phase 3: Fix and Verify (iterative loop)\n\n6. **Apply fixes** — remove deprecated code, translate renamed APIs, wire missing connections\n7. **Reload page in Playwright** — same record:\n   - Check console for errors\n   - Check network requests\n   - Take screenshot, compare with EUI baseline\n   - If something is still broken → collect new symptoms, diagnose, fix, repeat\n   - Do NOT move on until the current batch is verified working\n\n### Phase 4: Full Lifecycle Test\n\n8. **Test every user action** in DUI via Playwright:\n   - Load a record (fkey select) — fields populate, datagrid loads\n   - Add new record — form clears, fields editable\n   - Edit existing — fields become editable, save works\n   - Delete — record removed, form clears\n   - Navigate between records — state resets correctly\n9. **Compare each action with EUI** — same record, same action, screenshot both\n   - If behaviour differs → diagnose, fix, re-test\n\n### Phase 5: Record\n\n10. **Update `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml`** with any new patterns and symptoms discovered\n11. **Update page's migrator YAML** (`scripts/migrator/mod/<module>/<page>.yaml`) status\n\n## Classification Rules\n\n| Action | Meaning | What to do |\n|---|---|---|\n| translate | Direct DUI equivalent exists | Replace the call |\n| alias | Shim exists via `$.dui.shim()` | Leave for now, works. Mark for eventual cleanup |\n| deprecated | Plugin manages this globally | Remove from page entirely |\n| missing | No DUI equivalent | Stop and ask user |\n\n## Translation Map Rules\n\n- Map is **additive** — seeded from inv_gpass, grows with each page\n- The skill both **consumes and updates** the map in a single run\n- All shims MUST be registered via `$.dui.shim()` — no random global aliases\n- The YAML is the single source of truth for what shims exist and where\n- Each entry has: `match`, `action`, `symptoms`, `shim`, `dui`, `see_also`, `managed_by`, `notes`\n- Symptoms allow lookup by what you SEE (console error) not just what's in the code\n\n## Absolute Rules\n\n- Pages NEVER control buttons — not datagrid toolbar, not main toolbar, not butEn()\n- `loadData` is the one critical page-specific function — loads datagrid(s) on record select\n- `$.page.hook('afterLoad')` requires `$.page.register({ hooks: { afterLoad: fn } })` — migrator does NOT add this (known gap)\n- Screenshots go in `.pw/` directory\n- Browser viewport: 1600x900 minimum\n\n## Files\n\n- Translation map: `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml`\n- Skill: `/root/.claude/skills/fix-migrated-page/SKILL.md`\n- DUI login: `http://localhost:3333/?token=p4-agent-dev-token&ui=dui`\n- EUI login: use `/pure3d` skill for legacy server access"}
2026-02-27 16:31:06,832 14085 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'id': 452, 'text': '## Translation Map Seed Data\n\nCopy this YAML block directly into `docs/dui/migration-map.yaml` as the initial content.\n\nWhen encountering an unknown EUI call not in this map:\n1. Check `docs/dui/*.md` for the DUI equivalent\n2. Check `public/dui/js/plugins/` for existing shims (`grep dui.shim`)\n3. If not found, classify as `missing` and add to this file\n4. If a shim is needed, register it via `$.dui.shim()` in the correct plugin and record here\n\n```yaml\npatterns:\n  ajaxget:\n    match: "ajaxget("\n    action: alias\n    symptoms:\n      - "TypeError: ajaxget is not a function"\n      - "ReferenceError: ajaxget is not defined"\n    shim: { exists: true, name: ajaxget, registered_in: ajax-plugin.js }\n    dui: "$.dui.ajax()"\n    see_also: docs/dui/ajax.md\n    notes: "shim via $.dui.shim, deprecated"\n\n  clone:\n    match: "clone("\n    action: alias\n    symptoms:\n      - "TypeError: clone is not a function"\n    shim: { exists: true, name: clone, registered_in: utils.js }\n    dui: null\n    notes: "window.clone in utils.js, works as-is"\n\n  loadpage:\n    match: "loadpage("\n    action: alias\n    symptoms:\n      - "TypeError: loadpage is not a function"\n    shim: { exists: true, name: loadpage, registered_in: nav-plugin.js }\n    dui: null\n    notes: "shim exists, deprecated warning"\n\n  isronly:\n    match: "isronly("\n    action: alias\n    symptoms:\n      - "TypeError: isronly is not a function"\n    shim: { exists: true, name: isronly, registered_in: form-plugin.js }\n    dui: null\n    notes: "shim exists, deprecated warning"\n\n  getapp:\n    match: "getapp("\n    action: alias\n    symptoms:\n      - "TypeError: getapp is not a function"\n    shim: { exists: true, name: getapp, registered_in: page-plugin.js }\n    dui: null\n    notes: "shim exists, deprecated warning"\n\n  tbar_dgre:\n    match: ".tbar.dgre_"\n    action: deprecated\n    symptoms: []\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    managed_by: datagrid-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/datagrid.md\n    notes: "_sink Proxy absorbs silently. No error, just dead code. Remove."\n\n  linkbutton_enable:\n    match: ".linkbutton(\'enable\')"\n    action: deprecated\n    symptoms: []\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    managed_by: toolbar-plugin / datagrid-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/button.md\n    notes: "Plugins manage button state. Remove."\n\n  linkbutton_disable:\n    match: ".linkbutton(\'disable\')"\n    action: deprecated\n    symptoms: []\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    managed_by: toolbar-plugin / datagrid-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/button.md\n    notes: "Same as linkbutton_enable."\n\n  butEn:\n    match: "butEn("\n    action: deprecated\n    symptoms: []\n    shim: { exists: true, name: butEn, registered_in: toolbar-plugin.js }\n    managed_by: form-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/toolbar.md\n    notes: "Shim exists but gated by form state machine. Remove from pages."\n\n  _dgform_selector:\n    match: "#_dgform"\n    action: translate\n    symptoms:\n      - "jQuery selector returns empty — fields not updating in editor"\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    dui: "#<dgId>_editor"\n    see_also: docs/dui/datagrid.md\n    notes: "Replace with datagrid ID + _editor suffix."\n\n  textboxname:\n    match: "textboxname="\n    action: translate\n    symptoms:\n      - "jQuery selector returns empty — fields not found"\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    dui: "name="\n    notes: "EUI attr → standard name attr."\n\n  columns_inline:\n    match: "columns:[["\n    action: translate\n    symptoms:\n      - "Datagrid renders but columns don\'t match JSON config"\n      - "Duplicate or conflicting column definitions"\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    dui: "datagrid.<id>.json"\n    see_also: docs/dui/datagrid.md\n    notes: "Move to JSON config file."\n\n  rowEditor:\n    match: ".rowEditor("\n    action: deprecated\n    symptoms:\n      - "TypeError: $(...).rowEditor is not a function"\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    managed_by: datagrid-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/datagrid.md\n    notes: "DUI uses JSON config + editor modal. Remove."\n\n  editButs:\n    match: ".datagrid(\'editButs\')"\n    action: deprecated\n    symptoms: []\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    managed_by: datagrid-plugin\n    see_also: docs/dui/datagrid.md\n    notes: "DUI uses asdpx. Remove."\n\n  dwap_page_loadData_def:\n    match: "$.page.fn.loadData ="\n    action: translate\n    symptoms:\n      - "Datagrid stays empty after selecting a record"\n      - "No network request for datagrid data after record select"\n      - "afterLoad hook never fires"\n    shim: { exists: false }\n    dui: "$.page.register({ hooks: { afterLoad: fn } })"\n    notes: "Migrator misses this. Must register as hook."\n```'}
