2026-02-27 20:06:15,904 98303 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'patch-260227e — Convert bare input.easyui-combobox/datebox to +combobox/+datebox mixins', 'description': 'Add a pug fixer that converts bare `input.easyui-combobox` and `input.easyui-datebox` tags (outside `+fitem`) to their corresponding DUI mixin calls.\n\n## Problem\nThe migrator only handles container-level widgets (tabs, datagrid, layout) in `widgetMap`/`mixinMap`. Input-level widgets like combobox and datebox that appear as bare `input` tags (not inside `+fitem`) are only prefix-stripped — never converted to mixin calls.\n\nExample from `part_tracetrans_editor.pug`:\n- EUI: `input.easyui-combobox(_sqlid="inv^partid" name="pid")`\n- After migrator: `input.combobox(_sqlid="inv^partid" name="pid")` ← broken, not a mixin\n- Expected: `+combobox({_sqlid:\'inv^partid\', name:\'pid\'})`\n\nSame gap for datebox:\n- EUI: `input.easyui-datebox.today(name="sdate" style="width:100px;")`\n- After migrator: `input.datebox.today(name="sdate" style="width:100px;")` ← broken\n- Expected: `+datebox({name:\'sdate\', today:true, style:\'width:100px;\'})`\n\n## Scope\nNew fixer in `pug-fixers.js` that runs AFTER `fixEasyuiPrefixes` (Pass 4) — operates on already-stripped class names.\n\nWidgets to handle:\n- `input.combobox` → `+combobox({...attrs})`\n- `input.datebox` → `+datebox({...attrs})`\n- `input.numberbox` → `+input({class:\'numberbox\', ...attrs})` (if encountered)\n- `input.numberspinner` → `+input({class:\'numberspinner\', ...attrs})` (if encountered)\n\nSpecial handling:\n- `.today` class on datebox → `today:true` option\n- `_sqlid` attribute → preserve as `_sqlid` option\n- `name`, `style`, `required` etc → preserve as options\n- Skip lines already inside `+fitem` (those are handled by the fitem mixin\'s class detection)\n- Only target bare `input` tags at the pug line level'}
2026-02-27 20:06:28,809 98303 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 24, 'text': "## Investigation findings\n\n### Root cause\n`fixEasyuiWidgetDivs()` (pug-fixers.js L892-956) only has 5 entries in widgetMap: tabs, datagrid, filegrid, treegrid, layout. The AST `mixinMap` (L194-202) adds form and menu. Neither map includes any input-level widgets (combobox, datebox, numberbox, numberspinner, textbox, validatebox).\n\n`fixQbeToCombobox()` (L318-349) only processes lines containing the word `qbe` (L325: `if (!/\\bqbe\\b/.test(line)) continue`). Bare `input.easyui-combobox` tags without the `qbe` class are completely skipped.\n\n`fixEasyuiPrefixes()` (L400-413) strips the `easyui-` prefix globally — so `input.easyui-combobox` becomes `input.combobox`, but it's still a raw `input` tag, not a mixin call.\n\n### Affected EUI patterns (from grep of html/eui/)\nBare `input.easyui-combobox` — ~30+ occurrences across modules (toolbar filters, editor forms outside +fitem)\nBare `input.easyui-datebox` — ~15+ occurrences (date filters in toolbar areas)\nThese are typically in toolbar/filter areas, NOT inside `+fitem` calls.\n\n### Fix location\nNew function `fixBareInputWidgets()` in pug-fixers.js, inserted into the pipeline after Pass 4 (fixEasyuiPrefixes) since it needs the easyui- prefix already stripped.\n\nUses existing `parsePugTag()` helper to extract tag, classes, id, attrs from the line."}
2026-02-27 20:06:45,809 98303 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_complete args={'name': 'fix-part_tracetrans_editor'}
2026-02-27 20:10:33,841 98303 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 24, 'text': '## Implementation Plan\n\n### New function: `fixBareInputWidgets(lines)` in pug-fixers.js\n\nFollow `fixEasyuiWidgetDivs()` pattern (L892-956). Insert as **Pass 1c** — after `fixFormMixinToRawHtml` (1b), before `fixQbeToCombobox` (3), before `fixEasyuiPrefixes` (4). Runs on lines with `easyui-` prefix still present.\n\n**Widget map:**\n```js\nvar inputWidgetMap = {\n  \'easyui-combobox\':      \'combobox\',\n  \'easyui-datebox\':       \'datebox\',\n  \'easyui-textbox\':       \'input\',\n  \'easyui-numberbox\':     \'input\',\n  \'easyui-numberspinner\': \'input\',\n  \'easyui-validatebox\':   \'input\',\n};\n```\n\n**Logic per line:**\n1. Skip comments, skip `&attributes(...)` lines (mixin defs like ncr_inc.pug)\n2. `parsePugTag(line)` → extract tag, id, classes, attrStr\n3. If `tag !== \'input\'` → skip\n4. Find matching `easyui-*` class in classes[] or attr class value\n5. Look up mixin name from inputWidgetMap\n6. Remove widget class from classes array\n7. Special classes: `.today` → remove from classes, add `today:true` to attrs\n8. For `input` target (textbox/numberbox/etc): keep class name (minus easyui- prefix) as class attr\n9. Build mixin call — preserve #id, name, _sqlid, style, required, data-options as attrs\n\n**Example transformations:**\n- `input.easyui-combobox(_sqlid="inv^partid" name="pid")` → `+combobox({_sqlid:\'inv^partid\', name:\'pid\'})`\n- `input.easyui-datebox.today(name="sdate" style="width:100px;")` → `+datebox({name:\'sdate\', today:true, style:\'width:100px;\'})`\n- `input#classid.easyui-combobox(name="woclass" required="required")` → `+combobox#classid({name:\'woclass\', required:\'required\'})`\n- `input.easyui-textbox(name="DESCRIPTION" data-options="multiline:true")` → `+input({class:\'textbox\', name:\'DESCRIPTION\', data-options:"multiline:true"})`\n\n**Pipeline insertion in fixFile():** After Pass 1b, add Pass 1c call.\n**Export:** Add fixBareInputWidgets to module.exports.\n\n### Verification\n1. Run converter on part_tracetrans_editor\n2. Run on sa_operators, task_todo\n3. Verify pug compiles\n4. Increment SCRIPT_VERSION'}
