2026-02-28 07:44:58,260 98303 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_new args={'name': 'eui-discover-skill', 'title': 'Create /eui-discover skill — automated EUI baseline capture for migration and layout skills', 'steps': ['Design YAML schema for eui_baseline and dui_baseline sections', 'Create /eui-discover skill (SKILL.md)', 'Update /fix-migrated-page to consume eui_baseline and auto-invoke /eui-discover', 'Update /fix-layout to consume eui_baseline.layout_profile and auto-invoke /eui-discover', 'Test on inv/part_tracetrans_editor — run /eui-discover then verify both fix skills use the baseline']}
2026-02-28 07:45:04,030 98303 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Create /eui-discover skill that captures a complete EUI baseline for any page — screenshots, load elements, field values, tabs, datagrid columns, button inventory, layout profile. Store everything in the per-page migrator YAML (scripts/migrator/mod/<module>/<page>.yaml) so /fix-migrated-page and /fix-layout can consume it without re-opening EUI. Run once per page, reusable across sessions. Support batch mode for multiple pages.'}
2026-02-28 07:45:15,469 98303 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': "## What /eui-discover captures\n\n1. **Screenshots** — empty state + loaded state + each tab (paths stored in YAML)\n2. **Load element** — label, #id, selected record value (how you trigger data load)\n3. **Form fields** — 5-6 key fields: label, #id, value after load\n4. **Tabs** — label, #id, order, default active, screenshot per tab\n5. **Datagrid columns** — headers and order per grid\n6. **Button/action inventory** — custom buttons beyond standard toolbar, labels + #ids\n7. **Layout profile** — structural description: split type, panel arrangement, toolbar presence, grid count, tab count, form field count\n8. **Form state transitions** — what happens on Add/Save/Delete clicks\n\n## Cascade logic for consuming skills\n\n1. If `scripts/migrator/mod/<module>/<page>.yaml` doesn't exist → run migrator first\n2. If YAML exists but `eui_baseline` missing → run `/eui-discover`\n3. If both exist → proceed\n\n## dui_baseline\n\nAfter DUI fixes pass, a parallel `dui_baseline` section is populated with the same structure for ongoing comparison.\n\n## Key decisions\n\n- All data in per-page migrator YAML — single source of truth\n- Screenshots in .pw/ with consistent naming\n- /eui-discover can run standalone or be auto-invoked by fix skills\n- Support batch mode (list of pages or module name)"}
