2026-02-28 12:32:06,500 268582 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': "Investigation findings:\n\n1. Datagrid mixin already has a toolbar (`{dgId}_toolbar`) with Add/Edit/Delete buttons controlled by `asdpx`\n2. Line 73 has `block` — allows pug content appended to toolbar from page templates\n3. `<template>` elements used for row rendering (th/td/tr templates)\n4. Plugin wires toolbar via `initToolbar()` — finds `{dgId}_toolbar`, caches button refs\n5. `tbarEnable()`/`tbarDisable()` toggle `opacity-40 pointer-events-none` classes\n\nThe logins page doesn't use asdpx or JSON config — it builds datagrids entirely in JS with inline columns. So `hasToolbar` is false and no toolbar div is rendered.\n\nFor toolbut()-style custom buttons on datagrids:\n- Need a way for pages to declare custom toolbar buttons that get rendered server-side in the datagrid toolbar\n- The `block` at line 73 of datagrid.pug already supports this for pug-declared buttons\n- But for JS-declared buttons (toolbut pattern), need either:\n  a) A `<template>` for custom buttons that JS can clone and populate\n  b) Always render the toolbar container (even without asdpx) so JS can append to it\n  \nThe user's rule: any browser-side toolbar building MUST use `<template>`"}
