2026-02-28 14:06:44,972 268582 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 9, 'text': 'Two EUI patterns to handle:\n\n**Pattern A: `toolbar: [{...}]` in datagrid init**\n- EUI: `$(\'#dg\').datagrid({ toolbar: [{ iconCls:\'icon-add\', text:\'Add New\', handler:fn }] })`\n- Extractor should pull `id`, `text`, `iconCls` into JSON toolbar array\n- `handler` function stays in page JS — flag as manual, wire via `$(\'#btn_id\').on(\'click\', ...)`\n- Map `iconCls` → lucide icon name (icon-add→plus, icon-alert→message-square, etc.)\n\n**Pattern B: `toolbut([{...}])` standalone call**\n- EUI: `toolbut([{ id:\'but_x\', text:\'Foo\', iconCls:\'icon-bar\', onClick:fn }])`\n- These buttons logically belong to a datagrid toolbar — need to determine which datagrid\n- Extract `id`, `text`, `iconCls` into the datagrid\'s JSON toolbar array\n- `onClick` function stays in page JS — flag as manual\n\n**Migrator js-fixers.js changes:**\n- Strip `toolbar` property from inline datagrid init (it\'s now in JSON)\n- Strip `toolbut()` call entirely\n- Emit manual warning: "wire click handlers via $(\'#id\').on(\'click\', ...)"\n\n**Extractor changes (extract_datagrid_v2.js):**\n- When parsing datagrid init options, capture `toolbar` array if present\n- Extract static properties, skip functions\n- Write to JSON config alongside columns'}
2026-02-28 14:09:13,152 268582 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 8, 'id': 540, 'text': 'Changes needed:\n\n1. **datagrid.logins.json** — add toolbar array:\n   ```json\n   "toolbar": [\n     { "id": "but_user_msg", "text": "Message", "icon": "message-square", "disabled": true },\n     { "id": "but_user_logout", "text": "Logout", "icon": "log-out", "disabled": true }\n   ]\n   ```\n   (toolbar changes from `true` to an array — presence of array implies toolbar)\n\n2. **datagrid.pug mixin** — when `cfg.toolbar` is an array, iterate and render `+button` for each entry\n\n3. **datagrid-plugin.js** — `bindRowSelection`: enable/disable ALL buttons in toolbar div on select/unselect (not just asdpx _edit/_del). This is a plugin-level change that benefits all pages with custom toolbar buttons. Also disable all on `unselectAll`.\n\n4. **logins.pug** — remove the block content buttons (they come from JSON now)\n\n5. **logins.js** — remove `toolbut()` call (lines 234-301), remove `linkbutton(\'enable\'/\'disable\')` calls (lines 37, 195, 200, 270), wire click handlers via `$(\'#but_user_msg\').on(\'click\', ...)` and `$(\'#but_user_logout\').on(\'click\', ...)`'}
