2026-02-28 16:06:07,228 268582 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Research and document the complete EUI tree component — rendering, API, events, options — to prepare for building a DUI tree component that:\n1. Uses 100% DaisyUI markup and styles (ul.menu with details/summary nesting)\n2. Provides both static pug mixin (+tree) and dynamic JS API\n3. Keeps the same method names as EUI tree API, mapped to DUI elements\n4. Uses <template> elements for dynamic node creation\n5. Supports all tree variants: navigation, checkbox, checkbox+status icons\n\nScreenshots: `.pw/eui-tree-admin-files.png`, `eui-tree-admin-users-access.png`, `eui-tree-admin-users-access-expanded.png`, `eui-tree-admin-users-groups.png`, `eui-tree-admin-users-events.png`, `eui-tree-admin-users-reports.png`'}
2026-02-28 16:06:16,418 268582 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Research (steps 1-4) — CURRENT\n1. ✅ EUI tree screenshots — all tree variants captured from pure3d\n2. EUI tree JS API — full inventory of methods, events, options from jquery.easyui source\n3. DaisyUI tree markup — how to build trees with ul.menu + details/summary\n4. Existing DUI tree skeleton — audit current tree-plugin.js stub\n\n### Phase 2: Design (steps 5-6)\n5. Static tree mixin design — +tree(data, opts) pug mixin for server-rendered trees\n6. Dynamic JS API design — method-by-method mapping from EUI to DUI elements\n\n### Phase 3: Documentation (step 7)\n7. Write comprehensive notes with all findings, ready for implementation'}
