2026-02-28 16:13:02,396 268582 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 3, 'text': '## DaisyUI Tree Markup (uses `menu` component)\n\n**No standalone tree component in DaisyUI v5** — trees are built with `ul.menu` + `details/summary`.\n\n### Core Classes\n- `.menu` — on `<ul>` container\n- `.menu-active` — on `<a>` for selected state (primary color highlight)\n- `.menu-disabled` — on `<li>` for disabled state\n- `.menu-title` — on `<li>` for section headers\n- Size: `.menu-xs`, `.menu-sm`, `.menu-md`, `.menu-lg`, `.menu-xl`\n\n### Markup Patterns\n\n**Flat list:** `ul.menu > li > a`\n\n**Collapsible tree (key pattern):**\n```html\nul.menu\n  li\n    details(open)\n      summary Parent\n      ul.menu\n        li > a Child 1\n        li > a Child 2\n```\n\n**With checkbox:**\n```html\nli\n  label.flex.items-center.gap-2.cursor-pointer\n    input.checkbox.checkbox-sm(type="checkbox")\n    | Item text\n```\n\n**With icon:**\n```html\nli\n  a\n    span(data-lucide="box").w-5.h-5.flex-shrink-0\n    span Item text\n```\n\n**Active/selected:** `.menu-active` on the `<a>`, not the `<li>`\n\n### Key Design Points\n- Expand/collapse is native `<details>` — zero JS needed\n- `open` attribute controls expanded state\n- DaisyUI auto-adds disclosure arrow on `<summary>`\n- Nested `<ul class="menu">` goes INSIDE `<details>` after `<summary>`\n- Indentation handled automatically by CSS nesting'}
