2026-02-28 16:14:52,610 268582 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 6, 'text': '## Dynamic Tree JS API — EUI→DUI Method Mapping\n\n### Plugin: `public/dui/js/plugins/tree-plugin.js` (full rewrite)\n\n### DUI DOM Structure (target for all methods)\n```\nul.menu[id]                           ← tree container\n  template.tree-node-tpl              ← node template for dynamic creation\n  li[data-node-id]                    ← leaf node\n    a / label                         ← clickable element (.menu-active for selected)\n      span[data-lucide] .tree-icon    ← icon (optional)\n      input.checkbox                  ← checkbox (if checkbox mode)\n      span.tree-text                  ← text\n  li[data-node-id]                    ← branch node\n    details[open]                     ← expand/collapse (native HTML)\n      summary                         ← branch header (clickable)\n        span[data-lucide] .tree-icon\n        input.checkbox                ← checkbox (if checkbox mode)\n        span.tree-text\n      ul.menu                         ← children container\n        li ...                        ← recursive children\n```\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **`node.target` → `node.target`** — Keep the same pattern. Methods accept DOM elements, internally the plugin finds the `<li>` via `.closest(\'li\')`.\n\n2. **Expand/collapse uses `<details>` open attribute** — Not `.hide()/.show()`. Toggle via `details.open = true/false`. This means DaisyUI\'s disclosure arrow works natively.\n\n3. **Selection uses `.menu-active`** — Applied to the `<a>` or `<summary>` element inside the `<li>`.\n\n4. **Checkboxes are real `<input type="checkbox">`** — Not span-based fake checkboxes like EUI. Cascade logic handled in JS.\n\n5. **`<template>` for dynamic nodes** — `loadData()`, `append()`, `insert()` clone the template, set text/id/icon/checkbox, and insert into DOM.\n\n6. **Node data stored as `$.data(li, \'tree-node\')`** — Each `<li>` stores `{ id, text, iconCls, checked, attributes }`.\n\n### Method Mapping (EUI name → DUI implementation)\n\n#### Navigation & Query (read-only)\n| EUI Method | DUI Implementation |\n|------------|-------------------|\n| `find(id)` | `$tree.find(\'[data-node-id="\'+id+\'"]\')` → build node obj |\n| `getSelected()` | `$tree.find(\'.menu-active\').closest(\'li\')` → build node obj |\n| `getNode(target)` | `$(target).closest(\'li\').data(\'tree-node\')` |\n| `getData(target)` | Same as getNode — returns stored data |\n| `getRoots()` | `$tree.children(\'li\')` → map to node objects |\n| `getRoot(target)` | Walk up `.closest(\'li\')` chain to top `<li>` |\n| `getParent(target)` | `$(target).closest(\'li\').parent(\'ul.menu\').closest(\'li\')` |\n| `getChildren(target)` | `$(target).closest(\'li\').find(\'> details > ul > li, > ul > li\')` |\n| `getLevel(target)` | Count parent `<ul.menu>` elements between node and tree root |\n| `isLeaf(target)` | `$(target).closest(\'li\').find(\'> details\').length === 0` |\n| `getChecked(states?)` | `$tree.find(\'input.checkbox:checked\').closest(\'li\')` → map to nodes. With \'indeterminate\': also find `.indeterminate` |\n| `getLeafs()` | `$tree.find(\'li\').filter(no-details-child)` |\n\n#### Selection\n| EUI Method | DUI Implementation |\n|------------|-------------------|\n| `select(target)` | Remove `.menu-active` from all, add to target\'s `<a>`/`<summary>`. Fire `onSelect`. |\n| `lock(node?)` | Set `opts.locked = true`. If node, select first. |\n| `unlock(node?)` | Set `opts.locked = false`. If node, select first. |\n| `setFocus(id)` | `find(id)` → `expandTo()` → `select()` → `scrollTo()` |\n\n#### Expand/Collapse\n| EUI Method | DUI Implementation |\n|------------|-------------------|\n| `expand(target)` | `$(target).closest(\'li\').find(\'> details\')[0].open = true`. Fire `onExpand`. |\n| `collapse(target)` | `$(target).closest(\'li\').find(\'> details\')[0].open = false`. Fire `onCollapse`. |\n| `toggle(target)` | Toggle `details.open`. Fire appropriate event. |\n| `expandAll(target?)` | `$scope.find(\'details\').prop(\'open\', true)` |\n| `collapseAll(target?)` | `$scope.find(\'details\').prop(\'open\', false)` |\n| `expandTo(target)` | `$(target).parents(\'details\').prop(\'open\', true)` |\n| `scrollTo(target)` | `target.scrollIntoView({block:\'nearest\'})` |\n\n#### Checkbox\n| EUI Method | DUI Implementation |\n|------------|-------------------|\n| `check(target)` | Set `input.checkbox.checked = true`. If cascadeCheck: check all descendants. Update parent indeterminate. Fire `onCheck`. |\n| `uncheck(target)` | Set `input.checkbox.checked = false`. If cascadeCheck: uncheck all descendants. Update parent indeterminate. Fire `onCheck`. |\n\n**Cascade logic:**\n- When checking: check all descendant checkboxes\n- When unchecking: uncheck all descendant checkboxes  \n- After any change: walk up to each ancestor, count checked children. If all checked → parent checked. If some → parent indeterminate. If none → parent unchecked.\n- `onlyLeafCheck`: only render checkboxes on leaf nodes, branch nodes never get checkboxes\n\n#### Mutation\n| EUI Method | DUI Implementation |\n|------------|-------------------|\n| `loadData(data)` | Clear tree, recursively build nodes from `<template>`, append to tree |\n| `append({parent, data})` | Clone template for each data item, append to parent\'s `<ul.menu>` (create if missing) |\n| `insert({before/after, data})` | Clone template, insert before/after target `<li>` |\n| `remove(target)` | `$(target).closest(\'li\').remove()` |\n| `pop(target)` | Get node data, remove, return data |\n| `update({target, text, id, iconCls, ...})` | Update `<span.tree-text>`, `data-node-id`, icon, stored data |\n| `reload(target?)` | If url: AJAX fetch → `loadData()`. If target: reload that branch only. |\n\n#### Template-Based Node Creation\n```js\nfunction createNode(tree, nodeData) {\n  var tpl = tree.querySelector(\'template.tree-node-tpl\');\n  var li = tpl.content.firstElementChild.cloneNode(true);\n  li.setAttribute(\'data-node-id\', nodeData.id);\n  li.id = nodeData.id;\n  \n  var textEl = li.querySelector(\'.tree-text\');\n  textEl.textContent = nodeData.text;\n  \n  var iconEl = li.querySelector(\'.tree-icon\');\n  if (nodeData.iconCls) {\n    iconEl.setAttribute(\'data-lucide\', getIcon(nodeData.iconCls));\n  } else {\n    iconEl.remove();\n  }\n  \n  // If branch with children: wrap in <details>\n  if (nodeData.children && nodeData.children.length) {\n    var details = document.createElement(\'details\');\n    var summary = document.createElement(\'summary\');\n    // Move a/label content into summary...\n    var childUl = document.createElement(\'ul\');\n    childUl.className = \'menu\';\n    nodeData.children.forEach(function(child) {\n      childUl.appendChild(createNode(tree, child));\n    });\n    details.appendChild(summary);\n    details.appendChild(childUl);\n    li.innerHTML = \'\';\n    li.appendChild(details);\n    if (nodeData.state === \'open\') details.open = true;\n  }\n  \n  // Store node data\n  $(li).data(\'tree-node\', nodeData);\n  return li;\n}\n```\n\n### Events (matching EUI callbacks)\n| Event | When | Handler args |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| onSelect | Node selected | (node) |\n| onClick | Node clicked | (node) |\n| onDblClick | Node double-clicked | (node) |\n| onBeforeSelect | Before selection | (node) → return false to cancel |\n| onBeforeExpand | Before expand | (node) → return false to cancel |\n| onExpand | After expand | (node) |\n| onBeforeCollapse | Before collapse | (node) → return false to cancel |\n| onCollapse | After collapse | (node) |\n| onBeforeCheck | Before check toggle | (node, checked) → return false to cancel |\n| onCheck | After check toggle | (node, checked) |\n| onContextMenu | Right-click | (e, node) |\n| onLoadSuccess | After AJAX load | (node, data) |\n| onLoadError | AJAX error | () |\n\n### NOT implementing (Phase 1)\n- DnD (enableDnd/disableDnd) — not used in any active page\n- Inline editing (beginEdit/endEdit/cancelEdit) — not used in any active page\n- doFilter — nice-to-have, defer to Phase 2\n- move (up/down) — only used in one page, defer\n\n### Registration\n```js\n// At end of tree-plugin.js:\n$.dui.shim(\'tree\');\nif (dui._plugins) dui._plugins.loaded.push(\'tree-plugin\');\n```'}
