2026-03-01 12:52:38,564 416824 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_new args={'name': 'smart-migrate', 'title': 'Replace dumb migrator script with AI-driven /dui-migrate skill', 'steps': ['Design the skill — define inputs, process, outputs, and conversion rules', 'Write the /dui-migrate SKILL.md', 'Test on inv/part_plan — delete DUI files, run skill, compare output to EUI', 'Test on a second page (different structure) to verify generalization', 'Simplify the pipeline — remove/reduce audit+fix steps that exist only to fix script mistakes']}
2026-03-01 12:52:50,247 416824 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': "Replace the dumb regex-based migrator script (scripts/migrator/) with an AI-driven /dui-migrate skill that reads EUI source files and uses reasoning to produce correct DUI output the first time.\n\nThe current script gets ~70% right but creates systematic errors:\n- Converts easyui-qbe to combobox (completely different widget)\n- Puts #tbar as sibling of +datagrid instead of embedding it (toolbar:'#tbar' context lost)\n- Uses +fitem in toolbars with stacked layout instead of inline (doesn't understand toolbar context)\n- Cannot reason about JS context (which datagrid owns which toolbar, what formatters need)\n\nThese errors then require 3+ pipeline steps (audit, fix, fix-dgedit) to detect and repair — and as demonstrated on inv/part_plan, even those steps failed to catch the problems, hallucinating PASS.\n\nAn AI skill can read the EUI pug+JS, understand what each widget IS, consult the migration map and mixin signatures, and write correct DUI output. Scripts are dumb, skills are not."}
