2026-03-01 12:55:12,405 416824 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'smart-migrate', 'kind': 'plan', 'text': "## Approach: AI-driven /dui-migrate skill\n\n### Inputs (what the skill reads)\n1. **EUI pug** (`html/eui/<module>/<page>.pug`) — the source template\n2. **EUI JS** (`html/eui/<module>/js/<page>.js`) — datagrid inits, toolbar refs, formatters, event handlers\n3. **Migration map** (`docs/dui/migration-map.yaml`) — EUI→DUI pattern translations\n4. **Mixin signatures** — read actual mixin files (`html/dui/mixins/*.pug`) to know correct call syntax\n5. **Reference page** (`html/dui/mod/inv/sa_parts.pug` + JS) — known-good DUI page as a template\n6. **EUI baseline** from YAML — layout profile, load elements, field types (written by /dui-discover)\n\n### Conversion process (per-element reasoning)\nFor each element in the EUI pug, the skill:\n1. Identifies the widget type (qbe, combobox, datebox, textbox, datagrid, tree, menu, tabs)\n2. Looks up the migration map for the correct DUI equivalent\n3. Checks JS context — does the datagrid reference this element as toolbar? Does JS init it specially?\n4. Writes the correct DUI mixin call with correct arguments\n5. Handles toolbar context — if inside a toolbar, uses inline fitem layout, not stacked\n\nKey reasoning steps (what scripts cannot do):\n- `toolbar:'#tbar'` in JS → embed #tbar inside datagrid block, not as sibling\n- `easyui-qbe` class → must remain qbe, never convert to combobox\n- Toolbar form fields → inline layout (label left of input), not default fitem stacked\n- Datagrid formatters → extract to JSON config, preserve formatter function names\n- Panel regions → convert to +vsplit/+hsplit with +panel wrappers\n\n### Outputs (what the skill writes)\n1. **DUI pug** (`html/dui/mod/<module>/<page>.pug`) — complete template using correct mixins\n2. **DUI JS** (`html/dui/mod/<module>/js/<page>.js`) — translated page script using $.page patterns\n3. **Datagrid JSON** (`html/dui/mod/<module>/json/datagrid.<id>.json`) — column configs extracted from JS\n4. **Updated YAML** — sets dui_status, records what was generated\n\n### Pipeline simplification\nOnce the skill produces correct output:\n- /dui-audit becomes a lightweight sanity check (not a full structural comparison)\n- /dui-fix handles only edge cases the skill couldn't predict (runtime issues)\n- /dui-fix-dgedit may be absorbed into the skill (editor dialogs handled during migration)\n- The 7-step pipeline shrinks because most fix steps exist only to repair script mistakes\n\n### Testing strategy\n1. Delete existing DUI files for inv/part_plan, run skill, compare output to EUI\n2. Verify the 3 known failures are fixed: QBE preserved, toolbar embedded, filters inline\n3. Test on a structurally different page to verify generalization\n4. Run /dui-verify on the output to confirm functional correctness"}
