2026-03-01 13:32:35,488 416824 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'task': 'datagrid', 'title': 'Add JSON-defined toolbar filter fields — render QBE/combobox/datebox from datagrid config', 'description': 'The datagrid JSON config currently supports toolbar buttons (asdpx for CRUD, toolbar array for custom buttons) but NOT toolbar filter fields. Pages like part_plan, cp_plan, part_trace_history define filter toolbars (QBE, combobox, datebox) as pug block content inside +datagrid, which is fragile and requires per-page CSS fixes (justify-end collision, inline layout issues).\n\nEnhancement: Add a `toolbarFields` (or similar) key to the JSON config that declares filter components. The datagrid mixin renders them server-side using +fitem, eliminating per-page toolbar pug blocks. The page JS still wires onChange/reload behavior.\n\nExample JSON:\n```json\n{\n  "toolbarFields": [\n    { "label": "Part Filter", "type": "qbe", "id": "PART_ID_", "name": "PART_ID", "_sqlid": "inv^partid_qbe" },\n    { "label": "Product Code", "type": "combobox", "id": "PCODE_", "name": "PCODE", "_sqlid": "vwltsa^productcodeid", "editable": false, "required": true },\n    { "label": "Status Filter", "type": "combobox", "id": "REPORT_TYPE", "name": "REPORT_TYPE", "data": [{"text":"All Parts","value":"ALL"},{"text":"Shortages","value":"SHORTAGE"}], "editable": false }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nBenefits:\n- Eliminates per-page #tbar pug blocks for simple filter toolbars\n- Consistent left-aligned layout (no justify-end collision)\n- Consistent inline fitem layout (no {class:\'inline\'} mistakes)\n- Toolbar structure defined alongside columns in one JSON file\n- Reduces migration complexity — migrator just adds fields to JSON'}
2026-03-01 13:32:39,036 416824 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_switch args={'name': 'datagrid'}
2026-03-01 13:32:46,755 416824 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'task': 'datagrid', 'title': 'Add JSON-defined toolbar filter fields — render QBE/combobox/datebox from datagrid config', 'description': 'The datagrid JSON config currently supports toolbar buttons (asdpx for CRUD, toolbar array for custom buttons) but NOT toolbar filter fields. Pages like part_plan, cp_plan, part_trace_history define filter toolbars (QBE, combobox, datebox) as pug block content inside +datagrid, which is fragile and requires per-page CSS fixes (justify-end collision, inline layout issues).\n\nEnhancement: Add a `toolbarFields` (or similar) key to the JSON config that declares filter components. The datagrid mixin renders them server-side using +fitem, eliminating per-page toolbar pug blocks. The page JS still wires onChange/reload behavior.\n\nExample JSON:\n```json\n{\n  "toolbarFields": [\n    { "label": "Part Filter", "type": "qbe", "id": "PART_ID_", "name": "PART_ID", "_sqlid": "inv^partid_qbe" },\n    { "label": "Product Code", "type": "combobox", "id": "PCODE_", "name": "PCODE", "_sqlid": "vwltsa^productcodeid", "editable": false, "required": true },\n    { "label": "Status Filter", "type": "combobox", "id": "REPORT_TYPE", "name": "REPORT_TYPE", "data": [{"text":"All Parts","value":"ALL"},{"text":"Shortages","value":"SHORTAGE"}], "editable": false }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nBenefits:\n- Eliminates per-page #tbar pug blocks for simple filter toolbars\n- Consistent left-aligned layout (no justify-end collision)\n- Consistent inline fitem layout (no class:\'inline\' mistakes)\n- Toolbar structure defined alongside columns in one JSON file\n- Reduces migration complexity — migrator just adds fields to JSON\n\nFound during smart-migrate testing on inv/part_plan.'}
