2026-03-01 17:06:54,515 448637 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_new args={'name': 'migrate-jobplan', 'title': 'Migrate vwltsa/sa_jobplan — scheduling board with custom CSS and non-standard UI', 'steps': ['Audit and consolidate stylesheets (ulbar.css, sa_jobplan.css, inline block style)']}
2026-03-01 17:07:08,911 448637 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': "Migrate vwltsa/sa_jobplan (Job Planner) from EUI to DUI.\n\nThis is NOT a standard form+datagrid page. It is a custom scheduling board — a Gantt-chart-like matrix of resources × dates, with job operations rendered as colored `<li>` bars inside datagrid cells. The backend scheduler is untouched; this is purely a frontend/rendering migration.\n\n## Page characteristics (exceptions to standard pipeline)\n\n1. **ALL CSS is functional** — ulbar.css, sa_jobplan.css, and inline block style ARE the visual scheduling system. Nothing gets stripped.\n2. **No datagrid JSON extraction** — columns are dynamic (date-based), generated at runtime from server data via `$.page.fn.cols()`\n3. **No form fields, no standard lifecycle** — no Add/Save/Delete. Actions are AutoPlan, Apply, Unplan, Move, Lock/Unlock.\n4. **Auto-load page** — no user interaction needed to populate. `init()` fetches blank grid + operations on ready.\n5. **EUI datagrid is the rendering engine** — frozen columns (Resource ID, Units, Unplanned Jobs) + dynamic date columns. Custom cell formatters return `<ul>/<li>` HTML for job bars. DUI datagrid plugin compatibility must be verified.\n6. **EUI-specific APIs in heavy use**: `.menu('show')`, `.draggable()/.droppable()`, `.tooltip()`, `.window()`, `.linkbutton()`, `.progressbar()` — each needs a DUI strategy (shim, replace, or keep).\n7. **Namespace was mis-migrated** — previous pass did `dwap.` → `$.dui.` which is wrong. Needs `$.page.fn.*` and `$.page.ready`.\n8. **Included sub-files**: `capor_inc.pug`, `dg_resutil.pug`, `css/ulbar.css`, `css/sa_jobplan.css`\n9. **Conditional logic**: `planplus` license check controls standard vs Advanced Planner features.\n10. **Right-click context menu** with dynamic enable/disable based on job state.\n11. **Drag & drop** between cells (`.draggable()/.droppable()`) — switchable via bhave setting.\n12. **1031 lines of JS** with ~30 functions — all client-side display logic.\n\n## Discovery/verify skill exceptions\n\nStandard /dui-discover and /dui-test will NOT work as-is:\n- No load elements (auto-load)\n- No form fields to capture or compare\n- Dynamic columns (different every day)\n- No standard lifecycle\n- Screenshots are the only useful discovery output\n- Verification must be visual + functional (does the planner render, do buttons work) not field-by-field comparison"}
2026-03-01 17:07:50,893 448637 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Migration plan\n\n### Step 1: Audit and consolidate stylesheets (BEFORE any skills)\n- Read all 3 CSS sources: `html/eui/vwltsa/css/ulbar.css`, `html/eui/vwltsa/css/sa_jobplan.css`, inline `block style`\n- Classify every rule: functional (keep), EUI-framework (strip), potential DaisyUI conflict (flag)\n- Check for Tailwind utility collisions (`.active`, `.focus`, `bg-*` classes)\n- Check for EUI datagrid class dependencies (`.datagrid-cell`, `.datagrid-row`, `.datagrid-view1/.view2`)\n- Consolidate into DUI page stylesheet(s) under `html/dui/mod/vwltsa/css/`\n- Take EUI screenshot for visual reference baseline\n\n### Step 2: Fix JS namespace\n- `$.dui.page.*` → `$.page.fn.*`\n- `$.dui.bhave.*` → correct accessor\n- `$(document).ready` → `$.page.ready`\n- Pug line 9: `$.dui.page.planplus` → `$.page.fn.planplus`\n- Do NOT touch any logic — namespace only\n\n### Step 3: Fix pug template\n- Verify mixin usage is correct (+combobox, +linkbutton, +window, +tabs)\n- Fix any remaining EUI artifacts (data-easyui-warning flags)\n- Ensure included sub-files (capor_inc.pug, dg_resutil.pug) are also converted\n- Wire up consolidated CSS from step 1\n\n### Step 4: Verify under DUI\n- Load page under `?ui=dui`\n- Check: does the grid render, do job bars appear, do buttons work\n- Check console errors\n- Compare visually to EUI screenshot from step 1\n- Test: Resource/Job filter, AutoPlan, Apply, right-click menu, Priorities window\n\n### Step 5: EUI widget API audit\n- Catalog every EUI API call in the JS (.menu, .tooltip, .draggable, .droppable, .window, .linkbutton, .progressbar)\n- For each: does it work via DUI shim? Does DUI have an equivalent? Does it need a new shim?\n- Fix or shim as needed\n\nSteps 2-5 are provisional — step 1 must complete first to establish the CSS foundation.'}
2026-03-01 17:08:11,476 448637 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 1, 'text': "## Step 1: Audit and consolidate stylesheets\n\nDo this BEFORE running any pipeline skills (/dui-discover, /dui-migrate, /dui-test).\n\n### Source files to read\n1. `html/eui/vwltsa/css/ulbar.css` — job bar rendering system (li elements, colors, hover, drag proxy)\n2. `html/eui/vwltsa/css/sa_jobplan.css` — page-specific planner styles (capacity colors, day-of-week, etc.)\n3. Inline `block style` in `html/eui/vwltsa/sa_jobplan.pug` lines 95-152 — priority window, stats tooltip, lock indicators, group stripes\n4. Also inline `script.` block (lines 154-310) has EUI widget inits that reference CSS classes\n\n### Classification rules\n- **Functional (KEEP)**: ulbar li styling, capacity colors (capex/capmax/capor/capoff), job state colors (active, uplan, parop, days), lock indicator (slock::before/after), group stripes, drag proxy (.prox), hover highlight, progress background-size, priority styling, stats tooltip\n- **EUI-framework (STRIP)**: .datagrid-row-over (EUI hover style), any EUI panel/window chrome that DaisyUI replaces\n- **Conflict risk (FLAG)**: `.active` (Tailwind utility?), `.focus` (Tailwind ring?), `bg-*` classes (could collide with Tailwind bg-), `.bold`, `.center`\n\n### Tailwind/DaisyUI collision checks\n- `bg-red`, `bg-brn`, `bg-grn` etc. — these are custom planner color classes, NOT Tailwind utilities. Verify they don't collide.\n- `.active` — used on job bars for active jobs. Tailwind has no `.active` utility but DaisyUI might.\n- `.focus` — used for job focus highlighting. Could collide with Tailwind focus ring.\n\n### EUI datagrid class dependencies\nRules targeting these EUI classes must be preserved as-is because the EUI datagrid plugin generates this DOM:\n- `.datagrid-cell`, `.datagrid-row`, `.datagrid-row-over`\n- `.datagrid-view1`, `.datagrid-view2` (frozen vs scrollable)\n- `.datagrid-header`, `.datagrid-header-row`\n- `.datagrid-btable`\n- `td[field=...]` selectors\n\n### Output\n- Create `html/dui/mod/vwltsa/css/ulbar.css` — consolidated functional styles\n- Create `html/dui/mod/vwltsa/css/sa_jobplan.css` — page-specific functional styles\n- Update DUI pug to include these instead of EUI paths\n- Take EUI screenshot as visual baseline: `.pw/jobplan-eui-baseline.png`\n- Document any conflicts found and resolution decisions"}
